037e1d68-201c-4ebd-a7cf-28a8bf5b41c5 Gather all the ingredients.
037e1d68-201c-4ebd-a7cf-28a8bf5b41c5 Peel the sweet potato and cut into chunks. Cook in a pot of boiling water for about 10 minutes or until the sweet potato is tender. Mash with a potato masher and set aside to cool.
037e1d68-201c-4ebd-a7cf-28a8bf5b41c5 Drain and rinse the chickpeas and add them to a food processor.
037e1d68-201c-4ebd-a7cf-28a8bf5b41c5 Add the cooled mashed sweet potato, water, freshly squeezed lemon juice, tahini, garlic cloves, salt and pepper. Puree until smooth, scraping down the sides with a spatula as needed.
037e1d68-201c-4ebd-a7cf-28a8bf5b41c5 Serve with a drizzle of olive oil, if desired, alongside pita or naan bread and sliced vegetables.
9156ccfe-6a02-4204-91cd-89f516c6c669 Gather the ingredients.
9156ccfe-6a02-4204-91cd-89f516c6c669 To make the labneh, stir together the Greek style yogurt and salt until thoroughly combined.
9156ccfe-6a02-4204-91cd-89f516c6c669 Line a fine mesh strainer with cheesecloth and add the yogurt mixture. Tie the ends of the cheesecloth together and squeeze gently.
9156ccfe-6a02-4204-91cd-89f516c6c669 Place the strainer over a bowl but make sure the bottom of the strainer does not touch the bottom of the bowl. Leave sitting on the counter for one hour, draining off the liquid a few times. You can also do this in the refrigerator if the temperature is very hot but it will take a little longer. At the end of the hour, you'll have a soft batch of labneh.
9156ccfe-6a02-4204-91cd-89f516c6c669 To make the cranberry sauce, add the cranberries, sugar, water, lemon zest, lemon juice, cinnamon, cardamom and salt to a heavy bottom pot. Bring to a boil, stir well and reduce the heat to low. Allow to simmer for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the cranberries have popped. Remove from the heat and let cool before serving.
9156ccfe-6a02-4204-91cd-89f516c6c669 Spoon the labneh onto a plate or large bowl and swirl the cooled cranberry sauce into it. Serve with crackers as an appetizer with cocktails.
0059c03c-737e-499d-99c1-f721c49ca8c2 Make the falafel by adding the chickpeas, onion, garlic, cilantro or parsley, ground cumin, baking powder, salt, black pepper, flour, and red pepper flakes, if using. Puree until the mixture is mostly smooth but it does not need to be completely smooth. Refrigerate for at about 15 minutes.
0059c03c-737e-499d-99c1-f721c49ca8c2 While the falafel base is cooling in the fridge, make the tahini by combining the sesame paste, water, lemon juice, grated garlic, salt and pepper in a bowl.
0059c03c-737e-499d-99c1-f721c49ca8c2 Pre-heat the oven to 400 F. Toss the onion, bell pepper, and tomatoes in the olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Spread out on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and roast in the oven for about 30 minutes or until softened and lightly browned.
0059c03c-737e-499d-99c1-f721c49ca8c2 Add the two tablespoons of oil to a second sheet pan lined with parchment paper. Form the falafel into balls, approximately 1 ounce each (we used a cookie scoop) and gently roll them in the oil and place on the pan. Bake in the oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until the balls are a light golden brown.
0059c03c-737e-499d-99c1-f721c49ca8c2 Prepare the kebabs by alternating pieces of vegetables with falafel balls and drizzle with the tahini sauce.
0c91c7cb-7952-4adb-b5df-91f4ae58c605 Gather the ingredients.
0c91c7cb-7952-4adb-b5df-91f4ae58c605 Add 2 tablespoons of olive oil to a sauté pan. Heat on medium heat until hot. Add the garlic and chopped sage. Sauté until the garlic is browned. Remove the pan from the heat immediately.
0c91c7cb-7952-4adb-b5df-91f4ae58c605 Add the garbanzo beans, pumpkin purée, lemon juice, tahini, salt, pepper, cumin, and paprika to a high-speed blender or a food processor.
0c91c7cb-7952-4adb-b5df-91f4ae58c605 Begin blending. As you blend, drizzle in the remaining 1/4 cup of olive oil. Blend until completely smooth. Taste and add more salt to your liking.
0c91c7cb-7952-4adb-b5df-91f4ae58c605 Top the hummus with more olive oil, salt, paprika, chopped sage, and roasted pumpkin seeds if you wish. Serve with pita, pita chips, or fresh veggies for dipping.
b70a901e-1546-47e1-9578-bf43544bbe99 Gather the ingredients.
b70a901e-1546-47e1-9578-bf43544bbe99 Pre-heat the oven to 400 degrees.
b70a901e-1546-47e1-9578-bf43544bbe99 Wrap the beets tightly in aluminum foil and place on a baking dish to catch any drips. Roast in the oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until the tip of a knife easily pierces the beets. Remove from the oven and allow to cool enough to handle.
b70a901e-1546-47e1-9578-bf43544bbe99 Using a sharp paring knife, peel the beets (the peel should come off very easily) and cut into chunks.
b70a901e-1546-47e1-9578-bf43544bbe99 Add the chunks of beet to a food processor and puree. Then add the sesame paste, garlic clove, water and lemon juice. If you'd like the mixture thinner, continue adding water by the tablespoon until you've reached the desired consistency.
b70a901e-1546-47e1-9578-bf43544bbe99 Season with salt and pepper to taste and the red pepper flakes if using.
cdd1c31c-0b64-45fe-9026-a78794f6a2f6 Gather the ingredients.
cdd1c31c-0b64-45fe-9026-a78794f6a2f6 In a food processor, blend all ingredients together until smooth and creamy.
cdd1c31c-0b64-45fe-9026-a78794f6a2f6 Serve immediately with pita bread, pita chips, or vegetables.
cdd1c31c-0b64-45fe-9026-a78794f6a2f6 Enjoy!
74bfb3e5-a9ed-4ab6-ae89-9361a468aa05 Gather the ingredients.
74bfb3e5-a9ed-4ab6-ae89-9361a468aa05 Pre-heat the oven to 400 F..
74bfb3e5-a9ed-4ab6-ae89-9361a468aa05 Cut off the ends of each zucchini, slice in half, lengthwise, place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and drizzle on the olive oil.
74bfb3e5-a9ed-4ab6-ae89-9361a468aa05 Roast in the oven for 30 minutes or until the zucchinis are fully soft.
74bfb3e5-a9ed-4ab6-ae89-9361a468aa05 Allow the zucchini to cool enough to handle and then scoop the flesh out of each zucchini half.
74bfb3e5-a9ed-4ab6-ae89-9361a468aa05 Add the flesh to a food processor along with the garlic clove, tahini and lemon juice. Puree the mixture until smooth.
74bfb3e5-a9ed-4ab6-ae89-9361a468aa05 Stir in the chopped parsley, salt, ground black pepper and red pepper flakes, if using.
74bfb3e5-a9ed-4ab6-ae89-9361a468aa05 Serve with the toasted pine nuts alongside pita bread, naan or other flatbread for dipping.
e678bfe6-d65a-41f5-bab0-61e3e1d7c775 Gather the ingredients.
e678bfe6-d65a-41f5-bab0-61e3e1d7c775 Slice the avocado lengthwise, remove the pit and, using a spoon, scoop out the flesh.
e678bfe6-d65a-41f5-bab0-61e3e1d7c775 Add the avocado flesh, rinsed and drained chickpeas, sesame paste, peeled garlic cloves, lemon juice, water, salt, and black pepper to a food processor.
e678bfe6-d65a-41f5-bab0-61e3e1d7c775 Puree until completely smooth and adjust the salt and pepper to your liking.
e678bfe6-d65a-41f5-bab0-61e3e1d7c775 Stir in the chopped fresh dill and parsley. Top with a sprinkling of toasted pine nuts or pumpkin seeds, if desired.
e678bfe6-d65a-41f5-bab0-61e3e1d7c775 Serve as a dip with warm pita bread or toasted pita chips or spread on sandwiches. Store leftovers in the refrigerator in a lidded jar or seran wrapped bowl.
54c4388a-a823-4c11-adb3-313a08add6d6 Gather the ingredients.
54c4388a-a823-4c11-adb3-313a08add6d6 Drain the chickpeas and set aside the liquid from the can. Combine the drained chickpeas, lemon juice, sesame paste, crushed garlic and salt in a blender or food processor. Add 1/4 cup of the reserved liquid from the chickpeas. Blend for 3 to 5 minutes on low until thoroughly mixed and smooth.
54c4388a-a823-4c11-adb3-313a08add6d6 Place in a serving bowl, and create a shallow well in the center of the hummus.
54c4388a-a823-4c11-adb3-313a08add6d6 Add a small amount (1 to 2 tablespoons) of olive oil in the well. Garnish with parsley (optional).
54c4388a-a823-4c11-adb3-313a08add6d6 Serve immediately with fresh, warm or toasted pita bread, or cover and refrigerate.
0d09cac4-bdcf-4b2b-8f2f-791886b581be Gather the ingredients.
0d09cac4-bdcf-4b2b-8f2f-791886b581be In a food processor, blend the chickpeas, lemon juice, and olive oil. Add the garlic, cumin, salt and black pepper, then the sesame oil and water.
0d09cac4-bdcf-4b2b-8f2f-791886b581be Blend until you have a smooth paste.
0d09cac4-bdcf-4b2b-8f2f-791886b581be Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of water if mixture is too dry for your liking.
0d09cac4-bdcf-4b2b-8f2f-791886b581be Serve warm or at room temperature with fresh vegetables or pita bread for dipping.
0d09cac4-bdcf-4b2b-8f2f-791886b581be Enjoy!
f89f4ddd-b97b-4a33-8cd4-21115899d577 Gather the ingredients.
f89f4ddd-b97b-4a33-8cd4-21115899d577 Make the falafel by adding the chickpeas, onion, garlic, cilantro, parsley, ground cumin, baking powder, salt, black pepper, flour and red pepper flakes, if using. Puree until the mixture is mostly smooth but it does not need to be completely smooth. Refrigerate for at about 15 minutes.
f89f4ddd-b97b-4a33-8cd4-21115899d577 While the falafel base is cooling, make the tahini by combining the sesame paste, water, lemon juice, grated garlic, salt, and pepper in a bowl.
f89f4ddd-b97b-4a33-8cd4-21115899d577 Add about 2- to 3-inches of the canola oil to a large pot or deep sided pan and bring to a temperature of 350 F.
f89f4ddd-b97b-4a33-8cd4-21115899d577 Form the falafel into balls, approximately 1 oz. each (I used a cookie scoop) and place gently into the hot oil. Allow to fry for about 2 minutes and gently rotate the balls to continue frying on all sides. The falafel balls are done when they are a golden brown color all around.
f89f4ddd-b97b-4a33-8cd4-21115899d577 Remove from the oil with a slotted spoon and place on a paper towel to drain.
f89f4ddd-b97b-4a33-8cd4-21115899d577 Prepare the sliders by placing a bit of amba sauce on the bottom of each roll, then add a falafel ball and smash it down gently with the palm of your hand. Top with some of the diced cucumbers and a drizzle of tahini sauce.
717675e5-9779-4b7a-9394-8da42a4021f0 First, finely chop your garlic scapes by hand or in food processor.
717675e5-9779-4b7a-9394-8da42a4021f0 Next, add all of the remaining ingredients to either the food processor or blender and pulse until you get a creamy consistency.
717675e5-9779-4b7a-9394-8da42a4021f0 Feel free to add additional warm water if needed, in order to loosen the texture.
717675e5-9779-4b7a-9394-8da42a4021f0 Serve at room temperature immediately or store in refrigerator for serving in 1 to 2 days.
b914ffad-549c-4272-982e-d90ed4f99c86 To make the labneh, stir together the Greek-style yogurt, salt, dried oregano and chopped fresh parsley. Be sure the mixture is evenly incorporated to avoid pockets of salt.
b914ffad-549c-4272-982e-d90ed4f99c86 Pour the mixture into a piece of cheesecloth, tie the top and place over a strainer set over on a bowl. Be sure the bowl is large enough that the bottom of the strainer does not touch any dripping liquid. Leave the mixture out on the counter, at room temperature, for one hour to allow the bulk of the liquid to strain out.
b914ffad-549c-4272-982e-d90ed4f99c86 Drain the bowl and then set the whole thing in the refrigerator for approximately two days. Periodically drain any liquid that forms in the bottom of the bowl.
b914ffad-549c-4272-982e-d90ed4f99c86 When the labneh is ready and firm, remove it from the cheesecloth and set over a serving plate. Add the olive oil to a skillet or saute pan and add the sliced red onion. Saute on medium heat, stirring often, for about 15 minutes or until the onions are lightly caramelized.
b914ffad-549c-4272-982e-d90ed4f99c86 Pour the sauteed onions over the prepared labneh cheese and serve as a dip with crackers or slices of pita bread.
dfd45644-e41a-4560-9516-0140d303f3b7 Gather the ingredients.
dfd45644-e41a-4560-9516-0140d303f3b7 Preheat the oven to 375 F. Line one large or two medium baking sheets with foil.
dfd45644-e41a-4560-9516-0140d303f3b7 Stack the pita bread on a cutting board. With a sharp knife, cut the pitas into 6 even wedges. Gently open each wedge, and separate at the attached end, so that you get two pita triangles from each wedge. (You can also slice through the attached end with a sharp knife if you'd prefer.)
dfd45644-e41a-4560-9516-0140d303f3b7 Spread the pita triangles, inside (textured side) up, in a single layer on the baking sheet(s).
dfd45644-e41a-4560-9516-0140d303f3b7 Drizzle or brush the pita triangles lightly with the olive oil. Sprinkle liberally with the za'atar.
dfd45644-e41a-4560-9516-0140d303f3b7 Place the baking sheets into the preheated oven for about 5 minutes, or until the pita chips begin to turn crisp and lightly brown. (Watch the chips carefully if you leave them in longer—they can go from toasty to burnt in an instant.)
dfd45644-e41a-4560-9516-0140d303f3b7 Remove the baking sheets from the oven and place on racks to cool. (The chips will get crunchier as they cool).
dfd45644-e41a-4560-9516-0140d303f3b7 Serve warm or at room temperature with dips or soft cheeses.
dfd45644-e41a-4560-9516-0140d303f3b7 Enjoy!
42714f70-8881-4f39-ac36-d2c90b5d5757 Gather the ingredients.
42714f70-8881-4f39-ac36-d2c90b5d5757 In a food processor, combine the drained beans, tahini, spinach, garlic, olive oil, and lemon juice. Blend well.
42714f70-8881-4f39-ac36-d2c90b5d5757 Add cheese and red pepper flakes and blend into a smooth and creamy dip.
42714f70-8881-4f39-ac36-d2c90b5d5757 Serve with pita bread, pita chips, or fresh veggies.
a9e0bcc9-5bd1-4cb6-9838-66e0a26f65e6 Drain chickpeas and set aside liquid from can.
a9e0bcc9-5bd1-4cb6-9838-66e0a26f65e6 Combine remaining ingredients in blender or food processor.
a9e0bcc9-5bd1-4cb6-9838-66e0a26f65e6 Add 1/4 cup of liquid from chickpeas.
a9e0bcc9-5bd1-4cb6-9838-66e0a26f65e6 Blend for 3 to 5 minutes on low until thoroughly mixed and smooth.
c8e20986-95f1-4ac6-8bc7-8d8660a1d055 Place the chickpeas in a large bowl. Add enough cold water to cover the chickpeas by several inches. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap or a clean tea towel and allow to soak overnight.
c8e20986-95f1-4ac6-8bc7-8d8660a1d055 Drain and rinse the chickpeas. Place in a large stockpot, add the baking soda, and enough cold water to cover the chickpeas by 2 inches. Bring to a boil, skimming off any foam that rises to the top. Cover the pot, reduce the heat to low, and simmer for 45 minutes to an hour, or until the chickpeas are soft enough to crush between your fingers.
c8e20986-95f1-4ac6-8bc7-8d8660a1d055 Reserve about 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid, then drain and rinse the chickpeas. Reserve a tablespoon or two of the cooked chickpeas for garnish, if desired.
c8e20986-95f1-4ac6-8bc7-8d8660a1d055 Put the cooked chickpeas, tahini, lemon juice, garlic, salt, pepper, and paprika in a food processor. Purée until smooth. If the hummus is too thick or dry, add a bit of the cooking liquid, more lemon juice, or tahini to taste.
c8e20986-95f1-4ac6-8bc7-8d8660a1d055 To serve, place the hummus in a dish, and use the back of a spoon to make a shallow well in the center. Place any reserved chickpeas in the well, drizzle with olive oil, and garnish with freshly chopped parsley and regular or smoked paprika.
3a0a1252-cebe-4633-ba5b-171556e7271f Preheat the oven to 375 F. Use a fork to poke some holes in the eggplant skin.
3a0a1252-cebe-4633-ba5b-171556e7271f Place eggplant directly on the middle oven rack and roast for 30 minutes, or until the outside is crisp and the inside is soft. Allow it to cool for 20 minutes.
3a0a1252-cebe-4633-ba5b-171556e7271f Cut open the eggplant and scoop out the flesh into a colander; allow to drain for 10 minutes. (Removing the excess liquid helps to eliminate a bitter flavor.)
3a0a1252-cebe-4633-ba5b-171556e7271f Place the eggplant flesh in a medium bowl. Add the remaining ingredients except for the 1 tablespoon olive oil and mash together until the eggplant becomes paste-like. Alternatively, you can also use a food processor and pulse for about 2 minutes.
3a0a1252-cebe-4633-ba5b-171556e7271f Slowly add the olive oil and mix quickly and thoroughly to make sure it emulsifies along with the rest of the ingredients. If using a food processor, turn it on low as you pour the olive oil through the feed tube.
3a0a1252-cebe-4633-ba5b-171556e7271f Place the eggplant dip in a serving bowl and top with the garnish of lemon juice and olive oil. Add other garnishes according to taste.
3a0a1252-cebe-4633-ba5b-171556e7271f Serve with warm or toasted pita or flatbread. Enjoy!
3d08ad3c-df21-4245-856a-c5c36257193d In a food processor, combine all ingredients and process until smooth and creamy. If the hummus consistency is too thick, add 1 tablespoon water until desired consistency.
3d08ad3c-df21-4245-856a-c5c36257193d Serve sun dried tomato hummus immediately with hot pita bread, veggies, or pita chips.
bf4319a4-5246-4bdf-a9b2-5f71ab6d95ed Gather the ingredients.
bf4319a4-5246-4bdf-a9b2-5f71ab6d95ed Combine the chickpeas, warm water, peanut butter, olive oil, lemon or lime juice, crushed garlic and salt to a food processor. Blend to a very smooth, dip-like consistency. If it is too thick, add a bit more warm water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until the mixture has reached your desired level of thickness.
bf4319a4-5246-4bdf-a9b2-5f71ab6d95ed Serve peanut butter hummus with fresh celery sticks, carrot sticks, and broccoli florets. Warm pita or french bread cubes also go very well for dipping.
bf4319a4-5246-4bdf-a9b2-5f71ab6d95ed Many people sprinkle roasted chickpeas on top of traditional hummus, but you can sprinkle some roasted peanuts on top of this to add some texture and also indicate the flavor.
e8e50b34-a8bb-42a3-b0e6-51e734dcfde1 Gather seeds from watermelon and place in a colander. Be sure to use only the black seeds; do not use the small, white seeds. Rinse thoroughly in a colander to remove any excess watermelon.
e8e50b34-a8bb-42a3-b0e6-51e734dcfde1 Once clean, spread out in an even layer on a cookie sheet and allow to dry. Drying outdoors in direct sunlight is a good method. Seeds can be patted dry, but roast much better when they are completely dry.
e8e50b34-a8bb-42a3-b0e6-51e734dcfde1 In a frying pan on the stovetop, place watermelon seeds over medium-high heat and turn them over until seeds are roasted.
e8e50b34-a8bb-42a3-b0e6-51e734dcfde1 Add salt to the cup of water and stir until dissolved. Pour salt water into the frying pan and let cook, stirring occasionally until water has evaporated.
e8e50b34-a8bb-42a3-b0e6-51e734dcfde1 Once done, allow seeds to cool completely before eating.
0d62dee1-f1ff-4740-ab39-e7e1b96dcb33 Gather all of the ingredients.
0d62dee1-f1ff-4740-ab39-e7e1b96dcb33 In a food processor, process the garbanzo beans, minced garlic, chopped fresh spinach, tahini, and olive oil. Add the lemon juice and salt and blend until thoroughly smooth.
0d62dee1-f1ff-4740-ab39-e7e1b96dcb33 If your spinach hummus is too thick, try adding a tablespoon of water at a time until it is your desired consistency. The finished hummus should be smooth and creamy.
6dfd879b-b459-4375-b1c8-df0926b6211f In a food processor, combine chickpeas, artichokes, and tahini and blend.
6dfd879b-b459-4375-b1c8-df0926b6211f Slowly add olive oil, garlic, and lemon juice.
6dfd879b-b459-4375-b1c8-df0926b6211f Blend to a smooth consistency.
5c5a9037-2921-40c6-94eb-719a8594c56f In a food processor, process beans, garlic, olive oil, lemon juice, and oregano until desired consistency.
5c5a9037-2921-40c6-94eb-719a8594c56f If hummus is too thick, simply add olive oil in small increments (1/2 teaspoon) until desired consistency.
5c5a9037-2921-40c6-94eb-719a8594c56f Serve roasted garlic hummus garnished with finely chopped parsley with hot pita bread, pita chips, or veggies. Roasted red pepper hummus goes very well with cubes of warm Italian bread.
5c5a9037-2921-40c6-94eb-719a8594c56f Hummus can be prepared in advance up to two days if stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
5c5a9037-2921-40c6-94eb-719a8594c56f To serve, heat in the microwave or on a stovetop.
7599d040-6b59-4332-b69f-8bddfc63aa51 Gather the ingredients.
7599d040-6b59-4332-b69f-8bddfc63aa51 Grate zucchini and place in cheesecloth or absorbent paper towel. Squeeze out excess water. Place zucchini in a large bowl and add carrots and onions and toss gently.
7599d040-6b59-4332-b69f-8bddfc63aa51 Add dill weed, feta, flour, and eggs. Mix well. The mixture will become a thick batter.
7599d040-6b59-4332-b69f-8bddfc63aa51 Heat 1/2 cup olive oil in a frying pan. Pour 2 tablespoons of batter for each fritter. Fry on each side until golden brown.
7599d040-6b59-4332-b69f-8bddfc63aa51 Drain fritter on paper towels and serve immediately.
7599d040-6b59-4332-b69f-8bddfc63aa51 Enjoy!
2115ff2c-8366-4196-8fc5-7205332a2781 Preheat oven to 375 F.
2115ff2c-8366-4196-8fc5-7205332a2781 Spoon pizza sauce over pita rounds. Top with mozzarella and desired toppings.
2115ff2c-8366-4196-8fc5-7205332a2781 Place on baking sheet and cook for 7 to 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
2115ff2c-8366-4196-8fc5-7205332a2781 Serve immediately.
2115ff2c-8366-4196-8fc5-7205332a2781 Pita bread pizza is the perfect snack food! Try it with whole wheat pita bread for an even healthier version.
2436c3e2-035d-4b98-9002-a701c1cc24de In a food processor, combine all ingredients and blend into a creamy, smooth dip. If dip is too thick, add 1 tablespoon of water, until desired consistency.
2436c3e2-035d-4b98-9002-a701c1cc24de Kalamata olive hummus can be made up to two days in advance. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
2436c3e2-035d-4b98-9002-a701c1cc24de Kalamata olive hummus can be served hot or cold and with pita bread, pita chips, or veggies.
16d938f7-a372-4ec7-a721-3cb8de47581a Gather the ingredients.
16d938f7-a372-4ec7-a721-3cb8de47581a Finely chop tomatoes, cucumbers, and onions.
16d938f7-a372-4ec7-a721-3cb8de47581a Toss with remaining ingredients and gently mix well.
16d938f7-a372-4ec7-a721-3cb8de47581a Serve chilled.
4cb81053-583a-429d-9d9e-34d5ab27379d In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
4cb81053-583a-429d-9d9e-34d5ab27379d Allow chicken to marinate for 2 to 24 hours, covered in the refrigerator.
4cb81053-583a-429d-9d9e-34d5ab27379d Place chicken on the skewers (about 5 pieces on each).
4cb81053-583a-429d-9d9e-34d5ab27379d Grill for 15 minutes or until done. Remember to turn skewers during cooking.
4cb81053-583a-429d-9d9e-34d5ab27379d Serve shish taouk with a bed of rice, bread, and a salad. Enjoy!
714ed326-6555-427c-9b5f-bb6649839f62 Gather the ingredients.
714ed326-6555-427c-9b5f-bb6649839f62 Drain chickpeas and set aside liquid from the can.
714ed326-6555-427c-9b5f-bb6649839f62 Combine remaining ingredients in blender or food processor.
714ed326-6555-427c-9b5f-bb6649839f62 Add 1/4 cup of liquid from chickpeas. Blend for 3 to 5 minutes on low until thoroughly mixed and smooth.
714ed326-6555-427c-9b5f-bb6649839f62 Place in serving bowl, and create a shallow well in the center of the hummus.
714ed326-6555-427c-9b5f-bb6649839f62 Add a small amount (1 to 2 tablespoons) of olive oil in the well.
714ed326-6555-427c-9b5f-bb6649839f62 Serve immediately with fresh, warm or toasted pita bread, or cover and refrigerate.
714ed326-6555-427c-9b5f-bb6649839f62 Enjoy!
14e028f9-7567-4c8e-800e-593764fbbf0f In a food processor, combine garbanzo beans, tahini, lemon juice, and olive oil.
14e028f9-7567-4c8e-800e-593764fbbf0f Process until smooth.
14e028f9-7567-4c8e-800e-593764fbbf0f Add the roasted red peppers and garlic and continue pureeing until you've gotten your desired consistency.
14e028f9-7567-4c8e-800e-593764fbbf0f Garnish with parsley and serve warm or at room temperature with hot pita bread or toasted pita chips.
14e028f9-7567-4c8e-800e-593764fbbf0f Roasted red pepper hummus can be made up to two days in advance and stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
14e028f9-7567-4c8e-800e-593764fbbf0f Heat up in microwave or on stovetop to serve.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea Gather the ingredients.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea Cut the squash in half lengthwise.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea Gather seeds from squash, separating them from the stringy flesh, and place in a colander.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea Rinse the seeds thoroughly in a colander and pick away any excess squash flesh that is still clinging to the seeds.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea Once clean, spread out in an even layer on a clean kitchen towel or paper towels and allow them to dry. Seeds can be patted dry, but they roast much better when they are completely dry. This is a good step to reach before you continue to prepare the main flesh of your squash in whatever recipe you prefer. The seeds can be allowed to dry for 30 minutes to several hours before you go on to the roasting step.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea Preheat oven to 275 F.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea Toss the dry squash seeds with salt and butter and place in a single layer onto a cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil or parchment paper.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea Place in oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until seeds are golden brown.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea When you remove them from the oven, agitate the pan a bit to loosen them. Allow them to cool for 5 to 10 minutes before serving as they will become crisper as they cool.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea Serve the seeds warm or at room temperature. Save any roasted squash seeds in an air-tight container for several days. They are safe to store at room temperature.
5344a00b-fc1e-4a8a-a56d-c3dedabd3fea Enjoy!
a3dfb798-12c6-42a0-b0e4-12591a14d8d4 Make the pastry dough by adding the all-purpose flour, unsalted butter, baking powder, salt and fresh thyme to a food processor. Pulse a few times until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. With the food processor running, slowly pour the ice water through the feed tube and continue running just until a dough ball forms. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
a3dfb798-12c6-42a0-b0e4-12591a14d8d4 While the pastry is chilling, add the ground beef to a large saute pan along with the diced onions, minced garlic, ground cumin, garlic powder, fresh thyme, dried oregano, cayenne, ground black pepper and salt. Cook until the beef is browned and then stir in the beef stock and red wine. Continue cooking for another 5 minutes and then stir in the parsley. Remove from the heat and allow to cool.
a3dfb798-12c6-42a0-b0e4-12591a14d8d4 Pre-heat the oven to 400 degrees F.
a3dfb798-12c6-42a0-b0e4-12591a14d8d4 Roll out the pastry to about a 10" round and cut out 8 large (approx. 4") circles. Fill 4 of the circles with equal amounts of the cooled ground beef mixture and top with the remaining 4 circles. Use a fork to crimp the edges closed and place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake for 40 - 45 minutes or until the pastry is a light golden brown. Note that both the pastry and beef recipes can be doubled.
07518f31-47e8-4799-aac3-702e8eaec02a In a blender or food processor, process beans, garlic, jalapeno pepper, and olive oil.
07518f31-47e8-4799-aac3-702e8eaec02a Add lemon, tahini, and salt and blend well. Hummus should be smooth and creamy. If needed, add 1 teaspoon at a time until desired consistency.
07518f31-47e8-4799-aac3-702e8eaec02a Place in a bowl and serve with veggies, pita bread, or pita chips at room temperature. Hummus may also be stored in the refrigerator, covered.
cad7bcd1-f913-4dab-9210-88fb6dc26e10 Drain chickpeas and set aside liquid from the can.
cad7bcd1-f913-4dab-9210-88fb6dc26e10 Combine remaining ingredients in blender or food processor. Add 1/4 cup of liquid from chickpeas. Blend for 3 to 5 minutes on low until thoroughly mixed and smooth.
cad7bcd1-f913-4dab-9210-88fb6dc26e10 Place in serving bowl, and create a shallow well in the center of the hummus. Add a small amount (1 to 2 tablespoons) of olive oil in the well.
cad7bcd1-f913-4dab-9210-88fb6dc26e10 Garnish with extra cilantro (optional). Serve immediately with fresh, warm or toasted pita bread, or cover and refrigerate.
ed86fb6d-4259-424d-aea6-345929a7db5a Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 400 F.
ed86fb6d-4259-424d-aea6-345929a7db5a Add the butter to a pot and melt on the stovetop on low heat. Stir in the honey, sugar, water, cinnamon, salt, ginger, nutmeg, cardamom, and ground cloves. Continue stirring until melted and fully combined.
ed86fb6d-4259-424d-aea6-345929a7db5a Stir in the walnuts, almonds, and pistachios and spread out in a single layer on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
ed86fb6d-4259-424d-aea6-345929a7db5a Roast in the oven for 10 to 12 minutes, being careful not to burn the nuts.
ed86fb6d-4259-424d-aea6-345929a7db5a Sprinkle with the sea salt.
ed86fb6d-4259-424d-aea6-345929a7db5a Serve and enjoy!
fb47bfa5-3c29-42a4-8111-6a37dcee1e7d First, choose what type of hummus you would like to make your sandwich. Hummus is sold and can be prepared easily at home in a variety of flavors.
fb47bfa5-3c29-42a4-8111-6a37dcee1e7d If you are using pita bread, slice a small amount off the top, allowing the pita to be opened to stuff.
fb47bfa5-3c29-42a4-8111-6a37dcee1e7d With a butter knife spread the desired amount of hummus inside the pita pocket.
fb47bfa5-3c29-42a4-8111-6a37dcee1e7d Add chopped veggies and enjoy!
ad5cde32-aa4b-4963-b75a-157d1053c3a1 Gather the ingredients.
ad5cde32-aa4b-4963-b75a-157d1053c3a1 ​To Make the Hummus: add the rinsed and drained chickpeas, sesame paste, peeled garlic cloves, lemon juice, water, and salt and black pepper to a food processor. Puree until completely smooth and add any additional seasoning if needed. Scoop into a bowl and place in the refrigerator while you make the beef. (Note that the mixture will be quite loose but will firm up as it chills.)
ad5cde32-aa4b-4963-b75a-157d1053c3a1 To Make the Spicy Beef: add the ground beef to a large skillet or cast iron pan along with the onion, garlic, cumin, coriander, dried oregano, cayenne pepper, black pepper, salt, and baharat, if using. Saute, stirring often, until the meat browns.
ad5cde32-aa4b-4963-b75a-157d1053c3a1 Stir in the beef stock to moisten and bring the mixture together. Check the seasoning and balance out the flavors if needed. Keep warm.
ad5cde32-aa4b-4963-b75a-157d1053c3a1 Bring the hummus to room temperature and then spoon onto a deep plate or shallow bowl, leveling it off and creating a sort of divot in the middle. Add the beef to the center and serve warm with pita bread on the side.
c7b3e9a5-c998-46e8-9de9-79bf26f7973a Gather the ingredients.
c7b3e9a5-c998-46e8-9de9-79bf26f7973a Pre-heat the oven to 400 F.
c7b3e9a5-c998-46e8-9de9-79bf26f7973a To make the spice mix, combine all the spices in a small bowl. You'll have enough for this recipe, but I usually keep the same proportions but make a larger batch to have on hand.
c7b3e9a5-c998-46e8-9de9-79bf26f7973a Add the chickpeas to a large bowl, toss with the olive oil and spice mix.
c7b3e9a5-c998-46e8-9de9-79bf26f7973a Spread out on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and roast for 30 minutes.
c7b3e9a5-c998-46e8-9de9-79bf26f7973a Toss with the chopped herbs.
c7b3e9a5-c998-46e8-9de9-79bf26f7973a Serve on a bed of greens, over rice or in a pita sandwich with Israeli salad.
bb88967f-5d50-4890-8513-c3d183dd1656 In a blender or food processor, blend the white beans.
bb88967f-5d50-4890-8513-c3d183dd1656 Add tahini, lemon juice, cumin, garlic, olive oil, and salt until the ingredients form a creamy, paste-like consistency.
bb88967f-5d50-4890-8513-c3d183dd1656 Add small amounts of water as needed until desired texture.
bb88967f-5d50-4890-8513-c3d183dd1656 Pour the mixture into a large serving bowl. Cover and refrigerate for one hour or serve immediately.
15456b21-0e2b-4864-89c7-8f247725d61a Gather the ingredients.
15456b21-0e2b-4864-89c7-8f247725d61a Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor and blend to a smooth, creamy consistency. If too thick, add 1 teaspoon of warm water or chickpea liquid at a time and blend until desired consistency.
15456b21-0e2b-4864-89c7-8f247725d61a Serve almond butter hummus with pita bread, crackers, or fresh vegetables like carrots and celery.
98dd96b4-bca7-431e-92ac-d761e107d37e Peel and slice cucumbers into thin rounds.
98dd96b4-bca7-431e-92ac-d761e107d37e Place sliced cucumbers in a strainer and sprinkle with salt. Set aside.
98dd96b4-bca7-431e-92ac-d761e107d37e While salted cucumber slices sit, crush garlic and mash together with fresh mint leaves using a mortar and pestle or wooden spoon.
98dd96b4-bca7-431e-92ac-d761e107d37e Combine yogurt and garlic mint mixture together. Stir well.
98dd96b4-bca7-431e-92ac-d761e107d37e Fold in cucumber slices and serve cold.
c1b3e56a-f286-4e47-b391-558975abb30f In a blender or food processor, blend the chickpeas. Add tomatoes, olive oil, tahini, lemon juice, garlic, cumin, basil, and salt until the ingredients form a creamy, paste-like consistency.
c1b3e56a-f286-4e47-b391-558975abb30f Pour the mixture into a large serving bowl.
c1b3e56a-f286-4e47-b391-558975abb30f Cover and refrigerate for one hour before serving. This can be stored for up to 4 days.
ae14797a-21a2-4e2d-a039-78168567474b Gather the ingredients.
ae14797a-21a2-4e2d-a039-78168567474b Remove grape leaves from the jar and soak for a few hours in cold water. If not soaked properly, they will have a very salty taste.
ae14797a-21a2-4e2d-a039-78168567474b While grape leaves are soaking, mix together ground beef, tomato sauce, rice, parsley, coriander, salt, pepper and lemon juice. This is best done with your hands. Cover and place in refrigerator until ready to stuff leaves.
ae14797a-21a2-4e2d-a039-78168567474b Drain grape leaves and dry with paper towels. Remove stems. Place leaves shiny side down and have your meat mixture ready.
ae14797a-21a2-4e2d-a039-78168567474b Put about a teaspoon of mixture towards the bottom of the leaf. Fold in sides and roll upwards firmly. Do not roll too tightly. The rice does expand during cooking and may tear the leaf.
ae14797a-21a2-4e2d-a039-78168567474b Repeat with remaining leaves and mixture.
ae14797a-21a2-4e2d-a039-78168567474b In a large saucepan or dutch oven, place them side by side in circular layers. Place two lemon slices between the layers of grape leaves.
ae14797a-21a2-4e2d-a039-78168567474b Put a weight on top of the last layer of stuffed grape leaves—a ceramic plate works well. This ensures that the leaves to do not move around during cooking. Fill the pot with water, covering the leaves. Simmer and cook for 30 minutes on low until the rice is done.
ae14797a-21a2-4e2d-a039-78168567474b When rice is tender, remove vine leaves from the pot and serve.
ae14797a-21a2-4e2d-a039-78168567474b Enjoy!
ba93f740-2f48-450c-a658-2a63dddea6c4 In a blender or food processor, blend the chickpeas until smooth.
ba93f740-2f48-450c-a658-2a63dddea6c4 Add the tahini, lemon juice, olive oil, water, cumin, garlic, salt and yogurt.
ba93f740-2f48-450c-a658-2a63dddea6c4 Puree until the ingredients form a paste like consistency.
ba93f740-2f48-450c-a658-2a63dddea6c4 Pour the mixture into a large bowl and add stir in the parsley or cilantro and the chopped toasted pine nuts.
ba93f740-2f48-450c-a658-2a63dddea6c4 Garnish with any remaining parsley or cilantro.
ba93f740-2f48-450c-a658-2a63dddea6c4 Cover and refrigerate about an hour before serving with pita, nann or chips.
5c17ab41-5d15-454d-b4eb-c4256eac6014 Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 400 F.
5c17ab41-5d15-454d-b4eb-c4256eac6014 Place eggplant on a lightly greased baking sheet.
5c17ab41-5d15-454d-b4eb-c4256eac6014 Roast for 30 minutes, or until eggplant is tender. Remove from oven and allow to cool.
5c17ab41-5d15-454d-b4eb-c4256eac6014 Once eggplants have cooled, peel the skins. They should come off fairly easy. If you are having a tough time, just scoop the eggplant from the skin with a spoon. Set aside.
5c17ab41-5d15-454d-b4eb-c4256eac6014 In a food processor, combine and blend the tahini, garlic, and peppers.
5c17ab41-5d15-454d-b4eb-c4256eac6014 Add the eggplant and blend well.
5c17ab41-5d15-454d-b4eb-c4256eac6014 Add the olive oil.
5c17ab41-5d15-454d-b4eb-c4256eac6014 Transfer to a serving bowl. Stir in the lemon juice and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
5c17ab41-5d15-454d-b4eb-c4256eac6014 Serve immediately and enjoy.
399b4267-9570-401d-a141-871e2e37184e In a blender or food processor, blend soybeans, lemon juice, tahini, garlic, and salt until thoroughly mixed and smooth.
399b4267-9570-401d-a141-871e2e37184e Add liquid from soybeans until desired consistency, creamy and paste-like.
399b4267-9570-401d-a141-871e2e37184e Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate for about an hour.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Preheat the oven to 350 F.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Place the whole red peppers on a greased baking sheet.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Roast for about 10 to 12 minutes, turning approximately every four minutes. (If desired, you can also substitute jarred or deli ready-made roasted red peppers.)
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e In the meantime, place the breadcrumbs in a food processor and add 2 tablespoons of cold water.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Blend to make a puree.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Add more water as needed.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Remove the peppers from the oven and peel off the skin.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Cut open and remove the seeds.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Cut into pieces and add to the breadcrumb mixture in the food processor.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e In a small saute pan, saute the diced onions until lightly browned.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Add the sauteed onions and olive oil to the food processor and blend to a dip consistency.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Add the remaining ingredients and blend, adding olive oil as needed.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Remove from the food processor and place in a serving bowl.
549a600a-da69-4956-896e-e24f16773a9e Serve with pita wedges, veggies, or use as a dipping sauce for kebabs.
8452a6d5-1d09-4799-8bff-19f6b435cdf8 Gather the ingredients.
8452a6d5-1d09-4799-8bff-19f6b435cdf8 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
8452a6d5-1d09-4799-8bff-19f6b435cdf8 In a large bowl, combine the ground lamb, egg, garlic, ground cumin, ground coriander, smoked paprika, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper.
8452a6d5-1d09-4799-8bff-19f6b435cdf8 Place the mixture into an oiled 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and cook in the oven for approximately 30 minutes or until the top is a light golden brown.
8452a6d5-1d09-4799-8bff-19f6b435cdf8 You can slice the loaf immediately if you like but, for best results, cool completely, wrap in aluminum foil, and refrigerate until firm.
8452a6d5-1d09-4799-8bff-19f6b435cdf8 To reheat, add a little olive oil to a large skillet, slice the loaf very thinly and crisp up the slices in the hot pan for a few minutes.
8452a6d5-1d09-4799-8bff-19f6b435cdf8 Assemble the sandwiches with pita, warmed and toasted through. Spread on some tzatziki or tahini sauce, add lettuce, tomato, cucumber, onion, and top with more sauce.
8452a6d5-1d09-4799-8bff-19f6b435cdf8 Serve and enjoy.
ce12b147-61d5-491e-8b35-71d916ee035f Gather the ingredients.
ce12b147-61d5-491e-8b35-71d916ee035f In a large bowl, combine the ground lamb, minced onion and garlic, 1 teaspoon each of the ground cumin and sumac, salt, ground black pepper, red pepper flakes, and ice water.
ce12b147-61d5-491e-8b35-71d916ee035f Knead the mixture by hand until it turns tacky and starts sticking to the side of the bowl. Place in the refrigerator for about 30 minutes to chill.
ce12b147-61d5-491e-8b35-71d916ee035f Wet your hands and place a quarter of the lamb mixture onto each skewer. One easy way is to use a 1-ounce scoop to form balls, thread them onto the skewer, then mash them together.
ce12b147-61d5-491e-8b35-71d916ee035f In a small bowl, combine the remaining 1/2 teaspoon each of ground cumin and sumac.
ce12b147-61d5-491e-8b35-71d916ee035f Grill the kebabs for approximately 12 minutes, until well charred on both sides. Sprinkle the spice mix over the kebabs while they are cooking.
ce12b147-61d5-491e-8b35-71d916ee035f Serve the kebabs on warm pita or naan bread with sliced red onions, parsley, tomatoes, and diced cucumbers. Enjoy!
a42c912c-afe5-4681-9d20-7d4650a87255 Combine all ingredients except for beef, fillings, and sauce ingredients to make the marinade. If it seems a little dry, add a little olive oil (a tablespoon at a time). Here is an excellent tahini recipe, if you do not have some handy.
a42c912c-afe5-4681-9d20-7d4650a87255 Add the beef, cover, and refrigerate at least 8 hours, preferably overnight.
a42c912c-afe5-4681-9d20-7d4650a87255 In a stockpot or large saucepan, cook beef over medium heat for 45 minutes or until done. Be sure not to overcook! If beef becomes a little dry, add a few tablespoons of water throughout the cooking duration.
a42c912c-afe5-4681-9d20-7d4650a87255 While beef is cooking, prepare the sauce. Combine sauce ingredients and mix well. Set aside.
a42c912c-afe5-4681-9d20-7d4650a87255 Take the onions, tomatoes, cucumbers and sprinkle with sumac. Add other filling ingredients in a large bowl and combine well.
a42c912c-afe5-4681-9d20-7d4650a87255 When the beef is done, you can shred it, slice it, or leave into large pieces. As long as it is thinly cut, there is not much difference. We prefer to cut mine into wide strips.
a42c912c-afe5-4681-9d20-7d4650a87255 To assemble the pita, place enough beef on pita to cover 1/4 of the loaf. Add veggies and pour sauce. Roll like a soft taco or burrito and you have shawarma!
8c063a0c-0165-4ffc-8da0-41dcc67ad06e Gather the ingredients.
8c063a0c-0165-4ffc-8da0-41dcc67ad06e Add the onion, garlic, parsley, cilantro, cumin, coriander, salt, pepper, and flour to your food processor. Blend until very finely minced.
8c063a0c-0165-4ffc-8da0-41dcc67ad06e Dry the chickpeas as best as you can with paper towels. Add the chickpeas to the food processor and pulse gently until the chickpeas are just minced and blended with the spices. Do not over blend or it will become hummus!
8c063a0c-0165-4ffc-8da0-41dcc67ad06e Put the falafel mixture into a bowl, cover and refrigerate for about 2 hours.
8c063a0c-0165-4ffc-8da0-41dcc67ad06e Form the falafel into 12 balls, dusting with more whole wheat flour as needed. Use a cookie scoop to form the balls. Set them on a plate as you form them. Only form as many as will fit in the air fryer. Don’t form them all ahead of time to preserve their shape.
8c063a0c-0165-4ffc-8da0-41dcc67ad06e Preheat the air fryer to 350 F. Spritz the falafel balls with olive oil spray. Air fry the falafel for 15 minutes, turning half way through until lightly browned.
8c063a0c-0165-4ffc-8da0-41dcc67ad06e Allow to cool slightly in the air fryer basket.
8c063a0c-0165-4ffc-8da0-41dcc67ad06e Serve with pita, tzatziki, hummus, and fresh veggies. Stuff it in a pita or serve on top of a rice bowl.
87e359a5-f9fc-4136-89f4-5febfb313631 Gather the ingredients.
87e359a5-f9fc-4136-89f4-5febfb313631 Slice the cooked lamb shank as thinly as possible.
87e359a5-f9fc-4136-89f4-5febfb313631 Add the butter to a large sauté pan or cast iron skillet. Sauté the lamb slices in the butter until warmed through.
87e359a5-f9fc-4136-89f4-5febfb313631 Place the warmed lamb over the pita or naan bread.
87e359a5-f9fc-4136-89f4-5febfb313631 Add the seeded and diced tomatoes to the pan with the butter and sauté for a minute.
87e359a5-f9fc-4136-89f4-5febfb313631 Stir in the tomato sauce until warmed through.
87e359a5-f9fc-4136-89f4-5febfb313631 Season with salt and pepper to taste
87e359a5-f9fc-4136-89f4-5febfb313631 Pour the tomato mixture over the lamb
87e359a5-f9fc-4136-89f4-5febfb313631 Top with Greek-style yogurt and serve warm.
87e359a5-f9fc-4136-89f4-5febfb313631 Enjoy!
cce1c462-0ac3-42c1-b670-a484a12c5829 In a large bowl, add the ground lamb, diced onion, minced garlic, chopped parsley, ground cumin, ground coriander, ground cinnamon, salt, and pepper. Mix together until thoroughly combined and form four individual patties.
cce1c462-0ac3-42c1-b670-a484a12c5829 Heat up your grill or a grill pan if cooking indoors. Place the burgers on the grill and cook for 4 minutes, flip and cook for an additional 4 minutes. That will give you a medium-rare burger and an internal temperature of about 160 degrees Fahrenheit. Cook for an additional minute or two if you'd like your burgers more well done.
cce1c462-0ac3-42c1-b670-a484a12c5829 Toast or grill the buns until lightly golden brown (optional) and spread about a tablespoon of labneh on the bottom half of each bun. Place a cooked burger over the labneh, top with the lettuce or green of your choice and sprinkle the crumbled feta cheese over it. top with the remaining half of the bun and serve hot.
07479bbf-9647-428c-abd4-dfe4d45016dc Gather the ingredients.
07479bbf-9647-428c-abd4-dfe4d45016dc Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil and add the pasta. Cook according to the package directions.
07479bbf-9647-428c-abd4-dfe4d45016dc In a bowl, whisk together the sesame paste, water, soy sauce, lemon juice, honey, grated ginger, garlic, and crushed red pepper flakes until smooth.
07479bbf-9647-428c-abd4-dfe4d45016dc Drain the cooked noodles and toss with the tahini sauce. Top with the chopped scallions and sesame seeds.
07479bbf-9647-428c-abd4-dfe4d45016dc Serve and enjoy!
d171aa91-4965-4a51-83a5-a73764503a36 Gather the ingredients.
d171aa91-4965-4a51-83a5-a73764503a36 To bloom the saffron, crush the threads with your fingers and add them to a small bowl. Add the hot water and let sit for 15 minutes.
d171aa91-4965-4a51-83a5-a73764503a36 To prepare the chicken, heat the tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet and add the chicken, skin side down. Season with salt and pepper and cook until lightly golden brown on both sides, about 10 minutes. Remove from the pan and set aside.
d171aa91-4965-4a51-83a5-a73764503a36 Add the remaining tablespoon of olive oil to the pan along with the diced onion. Saute until the onion becomes translucent. Stir in the garlic and continue cooking for a few more seconds.
d171aa91-4965-4a51-83a5-a73764503a36 Stir in the tomato paste and then add the water, salt, black pepper, turmeric, and 2 tablespoons of the saffron water.
d171aa91-4965-4a51-83a5-a73764503a36 Add the chicken back into the pan, cover, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for approximately 30 to 40 minutes, until the chicken is tender and cooked through.
d171aa91-4965-4a51-83a5-a73764503a36 To make the saffron rice, add the rice and water to a pot and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce the heat to low and cook for approximately 15 minutes or until all the water has been absorbed. Remove from the heat, season with salt and the remaining tablespoon of the saffron water. Stir in the dried cranberries.
d171aa91-4965-4a51-83a5-a73764503a36 Serve the chicken and sauce over a bed of the rice.
c84c9228-1e3c-429b-a35e-2263b4bb491d Gather the ingredients.
c84c9228-1e3c-429b-a35e-2263b4bb491d Slice the eggplant into rounds and fry in the oil for about 5 to 7 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
c84c9228-1e3c-429b-a35e-2263b4bb491d Assemble the Israeli salad and stir together the tahini ingredients.
c84c9228-1e3c-429b-a35e-2263b4bb491d To assemble the sandwiches, spread the hummus evenly into the pita pockets and then stuff with the fried eggplant rounds and the sliced hard-boiled eggs. Spoon in the Israeli salad and drizzle with the tahini sauce and amba sauce.
12ef3f07-20ac-4c27-987a-248387ae8b28 Gather the ingredients. Pre-heat the oven to 350 F.
12ef3f07-20ac-4c27-987a-248387ae8b28 Add the broccoli rabe to a large pot of boiling water and cook for 2 minutes. Drain and set aside.
12ef3f07-20ac-4c27-987a-248387ae8b28 Add the tablespoon of olive oil along with the diced onions to a large oven-proof skillet or cast iron pan. Cook on medium heat for about 10 minutes or until the onions become translucent.
12ef3f07-20ac-4c27-987a-248387ae8b28 Add the minced garlic and continue cooking for about another minute.
12ef3f07-20ac-4c27-987a-248387ae8b28 Cut the par-cooked broccoli rabe into small pieces and stir into the onion and garlic mixture. Cook for a couple of minutes, then stir in the baby spinach leaves. Continue cooking for another couple of minutes, stirring often, until the spinach begins to wilt.
12ef3f07-20ac-4c27-987a-248387ae8b28 Stir in the ground cumin, salt, ground black pepper, and milk.
12ef3f07-20ac-4c27-987a-248387ae8b28 Make four wells in the mixture and crack an egg into each well, being careful not to break the yolks. Note that it is easier to crack each egg into a small bowl and then transfer to the pan.
12ef3f07-20ac-4c27-987a-248387ae8b28 Place the pan with the eggs into the pre-heated oven and cook for 10 to 15 minutes until the eggs are are set to your liking.
12ef3f07-20ac-4c27-987a-248387ae8b28 Sprinkle the cooked eggs with a dash of flaky sea salt and a pinch of red pepper flakes.
12ef3f07-20ac-4c27-987a-248387ae8b28 Serve with crusty bread or warmed slices of pita or naan.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Gather the ingredients.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Place dried chickpeas in a bowl and cover with cold water. Allow to soak overnight.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Drain the chickpeas and place them in a pot with fresh water. Bring to a boil.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Allow to boil for 5 minutes, then reduce the heat and let simmer on low for about 1 hour. Being careful not to overcook them. They should still be firm.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Drain and allow to cool in the strainer for 15 minutes.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Add 2 inches of oil to a heavy-bottomed large pot and heat to 350 F.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Combine the drained chickpeas, onion, garlic, parsley, cumin, coriander, salt, and pepper (if using) in a medium bowl. Add the flour.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Mash the chickpeas, mixing all of the ingredients together. Alternatively, you can combine the ingredients in a food processor. You want the result to be a thick paste.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Form the mixture into balls about the size of a ping pong ball. Slightly flatten.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Fry the falafel balls for 5 to 7 minutes until golden brown. Drain.
5eda6e55-7ac3-45e9-85e5-6b5546ea9697 Serve hot.
55e6d602-e891-4d85-bae8-2a3c4dbe0995 Gather ingredients.
55e6d602-e891-4d85-bae8-2a3c4dbe0995 Combine chickpeas, garlic, onion, parsley, coriander, cumin, salt, and pepper (to taste) in a medium bowl. Add flour and combine well.
55e6d602-e891-4d85-bae8-2a3c4dbe0995 Mash chickpeas, making sure to mix ingredients together. You can also combine ingredients in a food processor. You want the result to be a thick paste.
55e6d602-e891-4d85-bae8-2a3c4dbe0995 Form the mixture into the size of a ping-pong ball. Slightly flatten.
55e6d602-e891-4d85-bae8-2a3c4dbe0995 Fry in 2 inches of oil at 350 F until golden brown, about 2 to 5 minutes. Remove from the pan and drain on paper towels.
55e6d602-e891-4d85-bae8-2a3c4dbe0995 Serve falafel by itself, or with warm pita bread with veggies, or tahini sauce.
fbb937ad-cb8b-480f-8db3-3377b9a7b9f8 Gather the ingredients.
fbb937ad-cb8b-480f-8db3-3377b9a7b9f8 Heat a large frying pan or griddle to medium-high heat. Coat with olive oil and heat the pita rounds for 2 minutes on each side. The pita may begin to brown a little.
fbb937ad-cb8b-480f-8db3-3377b9a7b9f8 Heat up all the pita rounds and cut the top part to reveal the pocket.
fbb937ad-cb8b-480f-8db3-3377b9a7b9f8 Stuff each pita round with 3 falafel balls and a spoonful each of diced tomatoes and cucumber. Top with sliced onion, chopped parsley, the optional pickles, and a generous drizzle of tahini sauce.
fbb937ad-cb8b-480f-8db3-3377b9a7b9f8 Serve and enjoy.
fa26b42e-e4f4-43e3-9080-2b7944699c32 Add the 2 tablespoons of olive oil to a large pot or Dutch oven. Add the cubed stew meat and brown on all sides.
fa26b42e-e4f4-43e3-9080-2b7944699c32 Add in the chopped onion and minced garlic.
fa26b42e-e4f4-43e3-9080-2b7944699c32 Add the crushed tomatoes, stirring them in well with the meat, garlic, and onion.
fa26b42e-e4f4-43e3-9080-2b7944699c32 Add the ground cumin, ground coriander, ground allspice, salt, and pepper.
fa26b42e-e4f4-43e3-9080-2b7944699c32 Pour in the water and the tomato puree. Stir and combine well. Add the green beans and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 2 hours, or until meat is tender and done.
fa26b42e-e4f4-43e3-9080-2b7944699c32 The sauce should thicken slightly as it cooks. If it does not or if you would like a thicker sauce, whisk in a slurry comprised of 1/4 cup flour mixed with a little water until well combined. Then cook the sauce on high for a few minutes to allow the raw flour to cook out and the sauce to thicken.
fa26b42e-e4f4-43e3-9080-2b7944699c32 Serve the stew over white rice and alongside a green salad.
1de2ea5d-6e51-4d9a-951c-08659355fcc6 Gather the ingredients.
1de2ea5d-6e51-4d9a-951c-08659355fcc6 Up to 24 hours before grilling, combine marinade ingredients and pour into freezer bag.
1de2ea5d-6e51-4d9a-951c-08659355fcc6 Place lamb cubes in marinade and refrigerate until ready to grill. Be sure all pieces of lamb are coated well.
1de2ea5d-6e51-4d9a-951c-08659355fcc6 Prepare vegetables. Wash and dry veggies. Cut green peppers and onions into 1-inch chunks. Set aside.
1de2ea5d-6e51-4d9a-951c-08659355fcc6 Prepare skewers by spraying a light coat of cooking oil on them to prevent sticking.
1de2ea5d-6e51-4d9a-951c-08659355fcc6 Place lamb and vegetables on skewers.
1de2ea5d-6e51-4d9a-951c-08659355fcc6 Grill spicy lamb kebabs for about 5-7 minutes on each side or until done as desired.
1de2ea5d-6e51-4d9a-951c-08659355fcc6 Serve with hummus, baba ghannouj, or turkish cacik, a cucumber yogurt sauce for dipping.
e3fcb4c8-d5b1-4685-bfa0-81ba2efb009a Gather the ingredients.
e3fcb4c8-d5b1-4685-bfa0-81ba2efb009a Preheat pan or grill to 375 F.
e3fcb4c8-d5b1-4685-bfa0-81ba2efb009a In a bowl, combine lamb, parsley, salt, pepper, and paprika and mix well. (Roll up the sleeves, take off your rings, and do this by hand. The results are better this way.)
e3fcb4c8-d5b1-4685-bfa0-81ba2efb009a Form meat and spice mixture into 4 patties -- 1/2 to 3/4 inches thick.
e3fcb4c8-d5b1-4685-bfa0-81ba2efb009a Put in heated pan or grill and cook for about 4 to 5 minutes each side. The flavor of lamb is best at a medium-well, so cook until you see a faint pink color in the center. You can certainly cook longer, should you choose.
e3fcb4c8-d5b1-4685-bfa0-81ba2efb009a Place desired cheese on top and allow it to melt for about 30 seconds to one minute.
e3fcb4c8-d5b1-4685-bfa0-81ba2efb009a Splash the pan with some cool water to create steam and put a stainless steel mixing bowl over the pan for about 30 seconds. The result is a perfectly melted cheese that hugs the burger.
e3fcb4c8-d5b1-4685-bfa0-81ba2efb009a Serve and enjoy!
c6f0b997-19c4-4d1d-b63e-7b2b96af2ea7 Arrange chicken in a single layer in a glass baking dish.
c6f0b997-19c4-4d1d-b63e-7b2b96af2ea7 In a small bowl, whisk together cola, ketchup, apricot jam, onion, garlic, salt, pepper, and ginger to form the marinade.
c6f0b997-19c4-4d1d-b63e-7b2b96af2ea7 Pour the marinade over the chicken. Cover. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.
c6f0b997-19c4-4d1d-b63e-7b2b96af2ea7 When ready to cook, heat the oven to 375 F/190 C.
c6f0b997-19c4-4d1d-b63e-7b2b96af2ea7 Bake, covered, for 1 hour, basting after 30 minutes.
c6f0b997-19c4-4d1d-b63e-7b2b96af2ea7 Remove the foil. Bake uncovered for another 20 to 30 minutes, until the chicken is browned and cooked through.
c6f0b997-19c4-4d1d-b63e-7b2b96af2ea7 Serve with rice and enjoy.
d89e2592-655d-4623-8811-77992ff35323 In a bowl, combine lamb, olive oil, lemon juice, pepper, salt, and red pepper. Allow to marinate at least 2 to 3 hours prior to cooking.
d89e2592-655d-4623-8811-77992ff35323 Place marinated beef on skewers (about 6 cubes per skewer). Be sure to apply a light coat of oil on the skewer prior to threading the meat.
d89e2592-655d-4623-8811-77992ff35323 Place vegetables on separate skewers, alternating type of vegetable. The meat and veggies are cooked on different skewers because the meat will take longer to grill.
d89e2592-655d-4623-8811-77992ff35323 Cook lamb shashlik skewers on the grill or under the broiler for 10 to 12 minutes, or until desired doneness. Turn to ensure even cooking.
d89e2592-655d-4623-8811-77992ff35323 Grill vegetable skewers for last 5 minutes of grilling. Turn. The vegetables should be crisp, yet tender. Be careful not to overcook.
e8b00906-913e-446b-9117-859052dbf72f In a medium bowl, combine all chicken ingredients together and allow to marinate at least two hours.
e8b00906-913e-446b-9117-859052dbf72f Remove chicken from marinade and slice about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thin.
e8b00906-913e-446b-9117-859052dbf72f Pour 3 to 4 tablespoon of olive oil in a medium frying pan. Heat to a medium-high and add chicken. Cook chicken for about 8 minutes, stirring occasionally for even cooking.
e8b00906-913e-446b-9117-859052dbf72f In a medium bowl, combine chicken with veggies. Add desired sauce or condiment. Use desired amount.
e8b00906-913e-446b-9117-859052dbf72f Heat pita loaves in oven or microwave. Stuff pita with chicken and veggies.
e8b00906-913e-446b-9117-859052dbf72f Serve immediately with french fries.
5a391c97-3f28-4c9e-a7b3-860f561f9ad8 Gather the ingredients.
5a391c97-3f28-4c9e-a7b3-860f561f9ad8 2 hours prior to grilling, prepare fish by rinsing with cold water. Pat dry with paper towel. Cut into 1-inch cubes. Set aside.
5a391c97-3f28-4c9e-a7b3-860f561f9ad8 Mix olive oil, lemon juice, dill, and vinegar to make the marinade. Pour marinade into a large freezer bag and add fish. Make sure fish is well coated with marinade. Place freezer bag in the refrigerator for two hours.
5a391c97-3f28-4c9e-a7b3-860f561f9ad8 While fish is marinating, chop vegetables. Half the cucumber lengthwise and slice into 1/2 inch pieces. Cut the onions into eights. Cut red pepper into 1/3 chunks. Set aside.
5a391c97-3f28-4c9e-a7b3-860f561f9ad8 Remove fish from marinade. Discard marinade.
5a391c97-3f28-4c9e-a7b3-860f561f9ad8 Assemble kebabs according to taste. Many people like a combination of alternating pieces of meat and vegetables. This combination is entirely a matter of personal choice. It does not affect the cooking.
5a391c97-3f28-4c9e-a7b3-860f561f9ad8 If you are using steel skewers, be sure to put a light coat of oil on them before adding the fish and vegetables. They will slide on and off much easier.
5a391c97-3f28-4c9e-a7b3-860f561f9ad8 Spray the grill lightly with cooking oil and place the fish kebabs on the grill. Cook for about 4-6 minutes each side or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.
5a391c97-3f28-4c9e-a7b3-860f561f9ad8 Serve over white rice.
3a5d33f7-1c57-4626-8193-4837d0dd59e8 In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients. Combine well using a wooden spoon, or with your hands. Mixing with your hands allows the mixture to combine better.
3a5d33f7-1c57-4626-8193-4837d0dd59e8 Take about 1/4 meat mixture and make into a ball. Place ball through flat skewers, and shape into square cigar-like shapes. Repeat with remaining meat.
3a5d33f7-1c57-4626-8193-4837d0dd59e8 Place on grill and cook about 4 to 6 minutes each side, until meat is no longer pink and is done.
3a5d33f7-1c57-4626-8193-4837d0dd59e8 Serve over a bed of white rice and pita bread. Serve with a salad, like a fattoush or tabbouleh.
7adc7be7-3c45-460a-8d69-6c0b3cabfb85 Gather the ingredients.
7adc7be7-3c45-460a-8d69-6c0b3cabfb85 Soak the fava beans overnight in a large bowl of water.
7adc7be7-3c45-460a-8d69-6c0b3cabfb85 Drain the beans, add them to a large saucepan and cover them with fresh water. Bring the water to a boil and simmer on low for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until the beans are tender.
7adc7be7-3c45-460a-8d69-6c0b3cabfb85 Drain and place in a medium bowl. Add the crushed garlic, lemon juice, olive oil and cumin and toss well to combine and coat. It's common to mash the beans together with the other ingredients but you can also leave them whole and well mixed.
7adc7be7-3c45-460a-8d69-6c0b3cabfb85 Serve hot with a fried egg and pita bread.
7adc7be7-3c45-460a-8d69-6c0b3cabfb85 Enjoy!
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Gather the ingredients.
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Put flour in a shallow bowl.
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Beat eggs in a second shallow bowl.
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Mix bread crumbs with spices in a third shallow bowl.
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Beat chicken breasts to flatten.
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Dip chicken in flour, shaking off excess.
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Then dip in eggs, shaking off excess.
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Then dip in seasoned crumbs.
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Fry chicken in hot oil on both sides. Fry for 1 to 2 minutes per side or until golden brown.
1f30f535-da6f-45ec-a6f2-12b9995db689 Serve and enjoy!
09bf58c6-c186-4ec9-9515-0ca584f7a824 Soak beans overnight in water. Drain and rinse. Preheat oil to 350 F. 2 inches of oil in a frying pan will suffice. We prefer to use vegetable or canola oil, but olive oil can be used also.
09bf58c6-c186-4ec9-9515-0ca584f7a824 Place beans in food processor and blend. Add remaining ingredients to form a thick paste-like consistency. If too thick, add 1 tablespoon of water at a time until desired consistency.
09bf58c6-c186-4ec9-9515-0ca584f7a824 Remove falafel mixture from processor. Spoon falafel into hot oil by the tablespoon. Fry for about 2 minutes or until falafel is a golden brown color. Serve falafel by itself, or with hot pita bread with veggies, hummus, or tahini sauce.
46342100-2b8b-4030-acab-d85edfe781eb Cut the fish into 2x5-inch long pieces or fillets may be cut lengthwise in half. Set aside.
46342100-2b8b-4030-acab-d85edfe781eb Heat the oil in a large frying pan with 2-inch sides over medium-low heat. Add the garlic and onions and cook for 5 minutes.
46342100-2b8b-4030-acab-d85edfe781eb Add the red, orange, and yellow peppers and cook for another 4 minutes.
46342100-2b8b-4030-acab-d85edfe781eb Stir in the paprika, salt, and black pepper to taste.
46342100-2b8b-4030-acab-d85edfe781eb Stir in the chili powder or heat of choice. Add the water, increase the heat to medium-high, and bring to a boil.
46342100-2b8b-4030-acab-d85edfe781eb Reduce the heat to low, place the fish slices on top of the garlic, onions, and peppers, cover, and cook for 5 minutes.
46342100-2b8b-4030-acab-d85edfe781eb Use a fork to pick up some of the peppers and onions and place them on top of the fish slices. Cover and cook for another 5 minutes. Taste the sauce and add more salt if necessary.
46342100-2b8b-4030-acab-d85edfe781eb Sprinkle with the cilantro and serve. Serve warm or at room temperature.
dd7e62ec-858b-466b-a0d8-bcadad236f40 Heat oven to 350 F.
dd7e62ec-858b-466b-a0d8-bcadad236f40 In a food processor, combine the red bell pepper, parsley, garlic, pepper, and onion until thoroughly mixed. Ingredients can be used as listed but tend to hold better when mixed with the chicken.
dd7e62ec-858b-466b-a0d8-bcadad236f40 Pour the mixture into a large bowl and add chicken and mix well.
dd7e62ec-858b-466b-a0d8-bcadad236f40 Wet hands with water and form the mixture into balls, patties, or cigar-shaped pieces, whichever you desire.
dd7e62ec-858b-466b-a0d8-bcadad236f40 Place on greased cookie sheet or shallow baking dish in oven and cook for twenty minutes.
dd7e62ec-858b-466b-a0d8-bcadad236f40 Chicken kofta can also be cooked on a grill, either on skewers or alone, or pan-fried for 8 to 10 minutes, turning halfway through cook time.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Gather the ingredients. Heat oven to 425 F.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Bake sweet potatoes for one hour or until they can be pierced easily with a fork. Alternatively, you can microwave the sweet potatoes (usually 20 minutes for two large sweet potatoes, depending on your microwave). Allow sweet potatoes to cool completely.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Peel the skins off the cooled sweet potatoes and discard.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Place cooled sweet potatoes in a large bowl and mash with a fork.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Add flour, chickpeas, onion, garlic, parsley, cumin, coriander, lemon juice, and salt.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Continue to mash with a fork until well combined and smooth in consistency. Alternatively, pulse all of the ingredients in a food processor for quick mashing.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Lightly grease a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Using your hands, a melon baller, cookie scoop, or tablespoon, form the sweet potato mixture into small balls and place them 2 inches apart on the pan.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Sprinkle with the desired amount of sesame seeds.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Chill the falafel balls in the refrigerator for about 45 minutes.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Preheat oven to 375 F. Remove the chilled falafel balls from the refrigerator and bake for about 10 to 12 minutes or until golden and crispy.
bbf51f62-4d73-4a7e-8320-60f9e74ed048 Serve and enjoy.
3df674d7-f1bb-4407-80d9-8f6bcf530c96 Gather the ingredients.
3df674d7-f1bb-4407-80d9-8f6bcf530c96 Lightly toast the pita round in a toaster or oven and cut into bite size pieces.
3df674d7-f1bb-4407-80d9-8f6bcf530c96 Add the olive oil and minced garlic to a skillet or cast iron pan and sauté for a minute, just until the garlic becomes slightly translucent. Be careful not to burn it.
3df674d7-f1bb-4407-80d9-8f6bcf530c96 Add the diced tomato and continue cooking on medium low heat for another minute.
3df674d7-f1bb-4407-80d9-8f6bcf530c96 If the asparagus stems are thick, peel them with a vegetable peeler, then slice into thin diagonal pieces. Add to the pan and continue cooking for another minute.
3df674d7-f1bb-4407-80d9-8f6bcf530c96 Season with the sumac, salt, and pepper. Stir in the toasted pita bread pieces and cook for an additional minute or two until the pita absorbs the flavors.
3df674d7-f1bb-4407-80d9-8f6bcf530c96 Finish with the lemon juice and serve warm.
7cfa3cfa-d80c-482e-bad6-2583304c1683 Gather the ingredients.
7cfa3cfa-d80c-482e-bad6-2583304c1683 Preheat the oven to 400 F.
7cfa3cfa-d80c-482e-bad6-2583304c1683 In a small bowl, toss the chickpeas with the tablespoon of olive oil and the 1/2 teaspoon of Za'atar. Spread out on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. You can make the pita bowls at the same time.
7cfa3cfa-d80c-482e-bad6-2583304c1683 Rub both pitas with the tablespoon of olive oil and sprinkle evenly with the 1/2 teaspoon of Za'atar. Microwave for 20 seconds to make them pliable.
7cfa3cfa-d80c-482e-bad6-2583304c1683 To form the bowl, drape them over a small, oven-safe bowl or even the back of a muffin tin cup. If you have nothing like that, you can also form balls out of aluminum foil and drape the pitas over them. Bake both the chickpeas and pitas for 12 minutes.
7cfa3cfa-d80c-482e-bad6-2583304c1683 While the pita and chickpeas are in the oven, make the dressing by whisking together the olive oil, lemon juice, tahini, and Za'atar.
7cfa3cfa-d80c-482e-bad6-2583304c1683 When the pita bowls have cooled off enough to handle, assemble the salads by adding equal amounts of the baby spinach, tomatoes, cucumbers, red onion and roasted chickpeas to each pita bowl. Top with the vinaigrette.
7cfa3cfa-d80c-482e-bad6-2583304c1683 Serve and enjoy!
c0ac713d-a38d-49ae-a5f1-523b0f69de75 Finely chop the onion and parsley. Time-saving Tip: Use a food processor.
c0ac713d-a38d-49ae-a5f1-523b0f69de75 Add the ground beef to a large bowl and stir in the onions and parsley.
c0ac713d-a38d-49ae-a5f1-523b0f69de75 Season with salt and pepper.
c0ac713d-a38d-49ae-a5f1-523b0f69de75 Form the beef mixture into small balls and place four or five balls onto a metal skewer.
c0ac713d-a38d-49ae-a5f1-523b0f69de75 Shape the meat into a cigar shape on the skewer. Note: if you use wooden skewers, be sure to soak them in water for 30 minutes first to avoid them burning.
c0ac713d-a38d-49ae-a5f1-523b0f69de75 Pre-heat the oven to 350 F.
c0ac713d-a38d-49ae-a5f1-523b0f69de75 Bake the skewers for 45 minutes.
c0ac713d-a38d-49ae-a5f1-523b0f69de75 Or if grilling, grill for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
c0ac713d-a38d-49ae-a5f1-523b0f69de75 Serve over a bed of white rice.
e9cc8386-a877-4021-8997-dbd206140b4d Gather the ingredients.
e9cc8386-a877-4021-8997-dbd206140b4d Trim the lamb of all excess fat and cut it into 1-inch cubes. Cut the bell peppers and onions into 1-inch pieces.
e9cc8386-a877-4021-8997-dbd206140b4d In a small plastic or glass bowl, combine the marinade ingredients (olive oil, lemon juice, sea salt, cumin, grated ginger, and black pepper).
e9cc8386-a877-4021-8997-dbd206140b4d In a resealable container (a large zip-top bag works best), place the lamb pieces with the marinade. Massage them to mix and seal bag. Refrigerate the meat in the marinade for 2 to 24 hours.
e9cc8386-a877-4021-8997-dbd206140b4d Preheat the grill to high heat. Thread lamb, onion, and pepper pieces onto skewers, intermixing the pieces or making skewers of just meat and just vegetables (see Recipe Tip below).
e9cc8386-a877-4021-8997-dbd206140b4d Place the kebabs on the hot grill and cook for about 8 to 10 minutes, uncovered. Starting at the 2-minute mark, turn the skewers to cook another side of the cubes. Do this every 2 minutes until all four sides of the cubes have been grilled. Cook longer if lamb chunks are larger than 1-inch.
e9cc8386-a877-4021-8997-dbd206140b4d Once cooked to your desired doneness, remove the kebabs from the grill.
e9cc8386-a877-4021-8997-dbd206140b4d Serve on or off of the skewers, with lemon and lime slices.
56919918-2188-4a2a-84c4-6467b617f760 Gather the ingredients.
56919918-2188-4a2a-84c4-6467b617f760 Prepare the couscous. In a medium-sized saucepan over medium-high heat, heat 2 tablespoons olive oil. Add the couscous and cook, stirring occasionally, for about 3 to 4 minutes or until fragrant and lightly toasted.
56919918-2188-4a2a-84c4-6467b617f760 Add the vegetable broth, bring the mixture to a boil, and then turn down the heat and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed and the couscous is tender. Set aside.
56919918-2188-4a2a-84c4-6467b617f760 While the couscous simmers, heat the remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil in a saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the garlic, mushrooms, and white wine and cook, stirring often, for about 5 minutes.
56919918-2188-4a2a-84c4-6467b617f760 Add the dried thyme, fresh parsley, and salt, stirring to combine, and cook for about 3 to 4 minutes more, or until most of the moisture from the mushrooms has evaporated.
56919918-2188-4a2a-84c4-6467b617f760 Add the cooked Israeli couscous to the mushroom mixture, tossing well to combine. Add salt and pepper to taste.
a4057b5d-1d4e-4451-8d9c-e262e725d349 Combine the yogurt, salt, black pepper, turmeric, mustard, curry powder, cardamom, lemon juice, and vinegar in a large glass or plastic bowl.
a4057b5d-1d4e-4451-8d9c-e262e725d349 Add the cubed chicken into the bowl, toss to combine, cover with plastic wrap, and place in the refrigerator for 1 to 4 hours.
a4057b5d-1d4e-4451-8d9c-e262e725d349 Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.
a4057b5d-1d4e-4451-8d9c-e262e725d349 Remove the chicken pieces and thread onto skewers, alternating with the sliced onion, using about 5 pieces of chicken per skewer.
a4057b5d-1d4e-4451-8d9c-e262e725d349 Place the kebabs on the grill and cook for 10 to 12 minutes, turning occasionally, until cooked through and the internal temperature reaches 165 F.
a4057b5d-1d4e-4451-8d9c-e262e725d349 Remove from the heat and garnish with tomato slices, green pepper rings, and fresh mint or parsley.
01170ef0-0508-4a8f-a641-f955138e1271 Gather the ingredients.
01170ef0-0508-4a8f-a641-f955138e1271 Add the olive oil to a large soup pot along with the peeled and sliced onions.
01170ef0-0508-4a8f-a641-f955138e1271 Saute for a few minutes on medium heat until the onions begin to color.
01170ef0-0508-4a8f-a641-f955138e1271 Raise the heat and add the chicken stock, then the quartered potato, cauliflower florets, and cumin.
01170ef0-0508-4a8f-a641-f955138e1271 Bring to a boil, cover, reduce the heat to low and simmer for 25 minutes.
01170ef0-0508-4a8f-a641-f955138e1271 Using either an immersion (stick) blender or regular blender, puree the soup. Add the milk, salt, and pepper.
01170ef0-0508-4a8f-a641-f955138e1271 While the soup is cooking, combined the drained and rinsed chickpeas with the olive oil, cumin and garlic powder.
01170ef0-0508-4a8f-a641-f955138e1271 You can either spread them out on a baking sheet and roast in the oven at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or, as I did, use a cast iron pan on the stovetop and stir occasionally.
01170ef0-0508-4a8f-a641-f955138e1271 Season with salt and pepper and serve on top of the cooked soup.
01170ef0-0508-4a8f-a641-f955138e1271 Enjoy!
218bb41c-66dc-458f-9c3f-64f0750506bc Preheat the oven to 375 F.
218bb41c-66dc-458f-9c3f-64f0750506bc Season each lamb chop with an equal amount of the za'atar on both sides.
218bb41c-66dc-458f-9c3f-64f0750506bc Heat the olive oil in a large skillet or cast iron pan.
218bb41c-66dc-458f-9c3f-64f0750506bc When hot, add the lamb chops and sear on high heat for 2 minutes on each side.
218bb41c-66dc-458f-9c3f-64f0750506bc Place in the oven for 5 minutes, flip chops and continue cooking for an additional 5 minutes. Chops will be medium-rare at an internal temperature of 145 degrees, medium at 160 F and well done at 170 F. Continue cooking until you've reached your desired temperature.
218bb41c-66dc-458f-9c3f-64f0750506bc Remove the pan from the oven and move the cooked chops to a plate and cover with aluminum foil to keep warm while you make the sauce.
218bb41c-66dc-458f-9c3f-64f0750506bc Place the pan on medium-low heat on the stovetop and add the tablespoon of butter.
218bb41c-66dc-458f-9c3f-64f0750506bc Whisk in the flour until fully coated and then whisk in the beef stock.
218bb41c-66dc-458f-9c3f-64f0750506bc Continue cooking until the sauce has thickened.
218bb41c-66dc-458f-9c3f-64f0750506bc Season with additional salt and pepper, if needed, and pour over the cooked lamb.
85e696da-08fb-41d8-8b7f-1eb7663057d5 Preheat your oven to 400 F. Once the oven has preheated, arrange the 3 cloves garlic and red onion onto a small baking dish and roast for about 27 minutes, until fork-tender. Remove from the oven, but do not turn the oven off. Allow the garlic and red onion to cool for about 10 minutes.
85e696da-08fb-41d8-8b7f-1eb7663057d5 Place the roasted garlic and red onion into the bowl of a food processor along with the cooked chickpeas, ground coriander, ground cumin, and salt. Puree the chickpeas until smooth, stopping every 30 seconds or so to scrape the bowl of the food processor, or as needed. The mixture should be the consistency of a thick hummus after blending.
85e696da-08fb-41d8-8b7f-1eb7663057d5 Transfer the chickpea puree to a large bowl. Add the baking powder and chickpea flour and fold in gently to combine and distribute throughout the chickpea mixture. Fold in the chopped parsley and cilantro. Using very clean and dry hands, work the mixture into a dough, adding more chickpea flour as needed. Divide the dough into 2 inch balls and then press gently to shape into flattened pucks, about 1 1/2 inches wide.
85e696da-08fb-41d8-8b7f-1eb7663057d5 Arrange the unbaked falafel onto a parchment paper covered cookie sheet and lightly brush the tops of the falafel patties with 1/2 of the amount of cooking oil called for. Flip over and brush the other side of the falafel with the remaining oil—you may not need to use all of the oil called for. Sprinkle one side of the falafel patties with ground black pepper.
85e696da-08fb-41d8-8b7f-1eb7663057d5 Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes, then flip the falafel over and bake an additional 15 to 18 minutes, or until golden brown, fragrant, and baked throughout.
85e696da-08fb-41d8-8b7f-1eb7663057d5 Enjoy stuffed into a pita, on top of a salad, or as a quick and easy lunch on the go.
a6444a61-c1c1-40c3-bb9e-863991ca03b1 Gather the ingredients.
a6444a61-c1c1-40c3-bb9e-863991ca03b1 Drain lamb on a paper towel for 15 minutes.
a6444a61-c1c1-40c3-bb9e-863991ca03b1 Preheat grill.
a6444a61-c1c1-40c3-bb9e-863991ca03b1 Mix all ingredients together.
a6444a61-c1c1-40c3-bb9e-863991ca03b1 Mold mixture around long skewers.
a6444a61-c1c1-40c3-bb9e-863991ca03b1 Or, form the mixture into long thin sausages and thread onto skewers. The latter option is a bit more difficult for most people, but you select the option that best works for you. Note: only the ends of the skewers should be visible.
a6444a61-c1c1-40c3-bb9e-863991ca03b1 Place on grill and brush with oil and cook until done. The safe temperature for ground lamb is 165 F or 75 C.
a6444a61-c1c1-40c3-bb9e-863991ca03b1 Remove kofta from the skewers and serve.
a6444a61-c1c1-40c3-bb9e-863991ca03b1 Enjoy!
c4875ec2-1b1f-4965-af54-14c7259c56c4 Add the ground beef, ground cumin, garlic powder, ground coriander, dried oregano, black pepper, salt, and baharat, if using, to a bowl and mix well (clean hands work best for this).
c4875ec2-1b1f-4965-af54-14c7259c56c4 Form into 4 equal-sized patties.
c4875ec2-1b1f-4965-af54-14c7259c56c4 Place the patties on your grill pan (indoor or outdoor) and cook the burgers to your desired doneness.
c4875ec2-1b1f-4965-af54-14c7259c56c4 Assemble the burgers on the buns and top with an equal number of the greens, crumbled feta cheese, red onion and tahini sauce.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Gather the ingredients.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Preheat the oven to 400 F.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Combine 1 tablespoon of the olive oil with the teaspoon of cumin.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Peel and slice the carrots and toss them in the cumin oil.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, season with salt and pepper and roast in the oven for 30 minutes.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Add the farro, cover, reduce the heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Drain and return to the pot.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Add the remaining tablespoon of olive oil to a skillet or cast iron pan along with the sliced onion.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Saute for a few minutes until the onion is soft and a light golden brown.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Stir the sauteed onion into the cooked farro.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Make the cumin tahini sauce by combining the sesame paste, water, minced garlic, lemon juice and cumin in a bowl.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee Whisk until smooth and season with salt and pepper to taste.
f0f4b7fd-912b-4475-9e82-36a515c877ee To serve, spoon the farro and onion mixture onto a platter, top with the roasted carrots and drizzle with the tahini sauce. Enjoy!
97a9fc65-753a-4539-ba35-e80135e746e0 Toss the chicken strips in the canola oil and cumin. Place on a grill pan (or outdoor grill) and cook for a few minutes on each side until cooked through. Season with salt and pepper.
97a9fc65-753a-4539-ba35-e80135e746e0 Peel, seed and dice the cucumber or you can use an English seedless cucumber which does not require peeling or seeding.
