Peel and julienne the carrots, dice the tomatoes and peel and slice the red onion. Toss in a bowl with the red pepper flakes and parsley or cilantro.
97a9fc65-753a-4539-ba35-e80135e746e0 Make the dressing by combining the sesame paste, water, lemon juice, garlic powder and sumac. Stir until fully combined and season with salt and pepper.
97a9fc65-753a-4539-ba35-e80135e746e0 To assemble the tacos, divide the grilled chicken strips equally among the four pita rounds. Top with an equal amount of the vegetables and drizzle the tahini sauce on top.
9d598787-56a0-4d4b-88b5-320bca732263 Gather the ingredients.
9d598787-56a0-4d4b-88b5-320bca732263 Preheat oven to 400 F.
9d598787-56a0-4d4b-88b5-320bca732263 Lightly oil a baking pan and scatter the sliced onion across it. Lay the fillets side-by-side on the pan, on top of the onions, and sprinkle with the herbs and seasoning. Drizzle with olive oil and lemon.
9d598787-56a0-4d4b-88b5-320bca732263 Bake the fish for 10 minutes, or until it flakes easily with a fork.
9d598787-56a0-4d4b-88b5-320bca732263 While the fish is baking, whisk together the tahini and 1/4 cup of hot water. If the mixture is too thick, add additional water 1 tablespoon at a time until it is thick but creamy.
9d598787-56a0-4d4b-88b5-320bca732263 Add the garlic, olive oil and lemon juice and whisk thoroughly. If necessary, add warm water until the sauce reaches desired consistency. Add the parsley and seasonings to taste.
9d598787-56a0-4d4b-88b5-320bca732263 ﻿When the fish is cooked, top it with the sauce and serve immediately.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Gather the ingredients.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Make the garam masala by combining the spices until very fine, using a blender or a coffee grinder. Set aside.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Put the ginger, onions, and garlic into a blender, and mix to a paste, adding a tablespoon of water if necessary. Set aside.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Put the peppercorns, cloves, bay leaves, and cardamom pods in one bowl.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Put the ground cumin, ground coriander, cayenne, and 1 teaspoon of the salt in another bowl.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Put the yogurt into another bowl.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Wash and chop and drain the fresh spinach, have it ready to add into the dish. (Or defrost the frozen spinach.)
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Put the remaining teaspoon of salt into another bowl.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Heat the vegetable oil in a large Dutch oven.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 When hot, put in the peppercorns, cloves, bay leaves, and cardamom pods.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Stir for a second, put in the onions, garlic, and ginger. Stir and fry until the paste starts to develop brown specks.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Add the ground cumin, ground coriander, cayenne, and one teaspoon of the salt. Stir together, then add the meat. Stir and fry for a minute.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Next, add the yogurt one teaspoon at a time, until the yogurt has been mixed thoroughly with the other ingredients. Keep on frying until the meat has a slightly browned look.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Add the spinach, bit by bit, stirring in more as the spinach in the pan wilts. Keep stirring and cooking until the spinach wilts completely. It should give up its juices, to cook the meat.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Put the entire mixture in the slow cooker, and allow it to simmer for 6 to 8 hours on high or 8 to 10 hours on low until meat is tender.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 When done, sprinkle the garam masala over the meat, and stir in, then simmer for about 5 minutes longer. If there is too much liquid, simmer uncovered for 5 to 10 minutes until sauce is thicker.
06a1a4bb-f9b0-426a-9eb3-1b1e36ee1ef0 Enjoy.
a326212c-c9f8-4bb8-b332-4cd7ff7c0bd8 Gather the ingredients.
a326212c-c9f8-4bb8-b332-4cd7ff7c0bd8 Preheat the oven to 400 F.
a326212c-c9f8-4bb8-b332-4cd7ff7c0bd8 Spread the hummus evenly on the pita or naan bread. Sprinkle with the tomatoes, crumbled feta cheese, and za'atar.
a326212c-c9f8-4bb8-b332-4cd7ff7c0bd8 Place the pizza on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until the bread is a light golden brown.
a326212c-c9f8-4bb8-b332-4cd7ff7c0bd8 Remove from the oven and sprinkle with the chopped spinach.
a326212c-c9f8-4bb8-b332-4cd7ff7c0bd8 Serve and enjoy!
94585739-c93a-4566-8c69-bf74c856b68a Place stew beef, onions, garlic, salt, and pepper in a 3 quart pot. Add water to cover. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to simmer and cover. Simmer until meat is tender, about 30 minutes.
94585739-c93a-4566-8c69-bf74c856b68a When meat is tender, add okra.
94585739-c93a-4566-8c69-bf74c856b68a Once okra begins to become tender, about 10 minutes, add 1 can of crushed tomato/tomato sauce and mix well. Sauce will thicken as it cooks.
94585739-c93a-4566-8c69-bf74c856b68a Continue to simmer about an hour on low.
94585739-c93a-4566-8c69-bf74c856b68a Serve over cooked white rice, along with a salad, and pita bread.
1724a40f-548b-487b-bfa6-f9e8b9bc135e Prepare falafel, but do not fry yet.
1724a40f-548b-487b-bfa6-f9e8b9bc135e Chop and rinse vegetables. Toss together. Allow it to dry on a paper towel for a few minutes, while you fry your falafel.
1724a40f-548b-487b-bfa6-f9e8b9bc135e Fry falafel and allow to drain on paper towel.
1724a40f-548b-487b-bfa6-f9e8b9bc135e Lay a bed of lettuce/veggies on each serving plate.
1724a40f-548b-487b-bfa6-f9e8b9bc135e Add the desired amount of falafel rounds on top of lettuce.
1724a40f-548b-487b-bfa6-f9e8b9bc135e Sprinkle with tahini and falafel hot sauce.
bc9fa869-6e3e-4684-8c00-42c6590ac553 Turn on the broiler. Soak the bread in milk until all milk is absorbed, then mash it into a paste
bc9fa869-6e3e-4684-8c00-42c6590ac553 Process the parsley in a food processor and add to a large bowl with ground lamb and set aside.
bc9fa869-6e3e-4684-8c00-42c6590ac553 Process onion and garlic until very finely chopped. Add to bowl with bread and lamb mixture.
bc9fa869-6e3e-4684-8c00-42c6590ac553 Add the salt, cumin, sumac, cayenne pepper, allspice, pepper and mace and mix gently until the ingredients are well-combined.
bc9fa869-6e3e-4684-8c00-42c6590ac553 Put the mixture into a casserole dish and place under the broiler until browned, about 15 minutes.
bc9fa869-6e3e-4684-8c00-42c6590ac553 Remove from oven and reduce heat to 375 F.
bc9fa869-6e3e-4684-8c00-42c6590ac553 Slice the potato and tomato into pieces about 1/4-inch thick and add to the meat mixture, first a layer of potatoes and then of tomatoes.
bc9fa869-6e3e-4684-8c00-42c6590ac553 Cover the casserole with aluminum foil or a lid and cook on the middle rack of the oven for 40 minutes.
41b28ae8-d2db-4e86-97b2-6d5666a47aff Preheat oven to 350 F. Lightly grease a loaf pan.
41b28ae8-d2db-4e86-97b2-6d5666a47aff In a large bowl, combine lamb, beef, eggs, and breadcrumbs. Mix well. (Hands work best.)
41b28ae8-d2db-4e86-97b2-6d5666a47aff Add onion, green pepper, garlic, salt, pepper, cumin, basil, and cinnamon. Mix well, make sure spices are thoroughly spread throughout the mixture.
41b28ae8-d2db-4e86-97b2-6d5666a47aff Transfer mixture into prepared loaf pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until cooked through.
41b28ae8-d2db-4e86-97b2-6d5666a47aff Remove from oven and let stand approximately 15 minutes. Sprinkle with fresh, chopped parsley.
507410a0-6029-484e-9e3e-6582f1f7b68b Place the beef, chopped onion, minced garlic, salt, pepper and ground cumin, if using, into a 3-quart pot or Dutch oven. Add enough beef stock or water to cover the beef, bring to a boil, cover and reduce the heat to low. Simmer for about 30 to 45 minutes or until the meat is fork tender.
507410a0-6029-484e-9e3e-6582f1f7b68b When the meat is tender, add in the frozen spinach. No need to drain it. Once the spinach loosens up in the stew, add the crushed tomatoes or tomato sauce and mix well. Continue to simmer for an additional hour on low heat.
507410a0-6029-484e-9e3e-6582f1f7b68b Serve the stew over cooked white rice, pasta or mashed potatoes alongside a simple salad.
d55a177c-0d9c-42df-b9e0-09f7a6796e5a Gather the ingredients.
d55a177c-0d9c-42df-b9e0-09f7a6796e5a In a large saucepan, brown meat with olive oil. Add onions and garlic.
d55a177c-0d9c-42df-b9e0-09f7a6796e5a Add crushed tomatoes, stirring well with meat, garlic and onion. Add cumin, coriander, salt and pepper, and allspice. Add water and tomato puree. Stir and combine well.
d55a177c-0d9c-42df-b9e0-09f7a6796e5a Add okra and bring to a boil.
d55a177c-0d9c-42df-b9e0-09f7a6796e5a Reduce heat to low and simmer for 2 hours, or until meat is tender and done.
d55a177c-0d9c-42df-b9e0-09f7a6796e5a The sauce should thicken as it cooks. If it does not, add 1/2 cup all-purpose flour.
d55a177c-0d9c-42df-b9e0-09f7a6796e5a Serve bamia with white rice and a salad. Enjoy!
1f5b7af0-a08b-4912-b808-a9628d740e65 Gather the ingredients.
1f5b7af0-a08b-4912-b808-a9628d740e65 Combine the ground black pepper, ground coriander, ground cumin, lemon juice and oil in a medium bowl.
1f5b7af0-a08b-4912-b808-a9628d740e65 Add the lamb chops, cover and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour, but up to 24 hours.
1f5b7af0-a08b-4912-b808-a9628d740e65 Cook the lamb chops for 5 to 7 minutes on each side on the grill or under the broiler in the oven. Season with salt.
1f5b7af0-a08b-4912-b808-a9628d740e65 Serve with white rice, salad, and pita bread. You can also serve with fried potatoes for an informal meal or cookout.
1f5b7af0-a08b-4912-b808-a9628d740e65 Enjoy!
d0852442-f0b3-43ab-ad80-7ff97f566414 Gather the ingredients.
d0852442-f0b3-43ab-ad80-7ff97f566414 In a saucepan, bring water to a boil.
d0852442-f0b3-43ab-ad80-7ff97f566414 Add salt and stir. Add couscous and cover. Remove from heat and allow to sit for about 5 to 6 minutes.
d0852442-f0b3-43ab-ad80-7ff97f566414 Allow the couscous to absorb the water and then fluff with a fork. Couscous should be light and fluffy, not gummy.
d0852442-f0b3-43ab-ad80-7ff97f566414 Serve as the base for a stew or as a side dish. Enjoy!
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Oil a 9 x 13 2-inch baking dish or a similarly-sized (3 to 4-quart) casserole dish.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Line 2 large, rimmed baking sheets with parchment paper. Divide the challah cubes between the baking sheets.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Drizzle the bread with a little olive oil, toss with clean hands, and spread evenly into a single layer. Bake, turning once or twice while cooking, until dry and toasted, about 15 to 20 minutes. Set aside to cool, but leave the oven on.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f In a large skillet or pan set over medium-high heat, warm the oil. Add the onion, garlic, fennel, and celery, and saute until the onion is soft and translucent, about 5 minutes.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Add apple and continue to saute until warmed through, about 5 minutes more. Stir in the sage and lemon zest and saute until fragrant, about 1 minute. Remove from the heat.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Place the toasted challah cubes in a large bowl. Add the sauteed vegetables and toss to coat.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Pour the vegetable broth evenly over the mixture and stir well. Season to taste with salt and pepper, if desired.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Pour the stuffing mixture into the prepared baking dish and smooth the top. Drizzle with a little olive oil.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Cover with foil and bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Carefully remove the foil and bake for 10 to 20 minutes more, or until the top is golden, and the stuffing reaches your preferred consistency.
c5238f04-5ec4-49ef-bf8e-925cb14f008f Serve and enjoy!
96bebe60-8842-4857-8b2b-2bc85ace5487 Gather the ingredients.
96bebe60-8842-4857-8b2b-2bc85ace5487 Lightly grease a tube pan or 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with oil or non-stick cooking spray. Preheat the oven to 350 F (180 C).
96bebe60-8842-4857-8b2b-2bc85ace5487 In a large pot, bring water to a boil. Add the noodles, and cook according to the package directions, taking care not to overcook.
96bebe60-8842-4857-8b2b-2bc85ace5487 Drain, return to the pot, and stir in 1 tablespoon of oil to prevent the noodles from sticking. Then, set it aside.
96bebe60-8842-4857-8b2b-2bc85ace5487 Place the oil and sugar in a light-colored, heavy-bottomed saucepan, which will allow you to see the color of the melting sugar. Adjust the stove to medium heat, and stir continuously with a wooden spoon. Slowly the sugar will start to turn yellowish-brown, combining with the oil. If the sugar turns dark brown too quickly, turn the heat down.
96bebe60-8842-4857-8b2b-2bc85ace5487 Stir until a bubbly, liquid caramel has formed. Then immediately pour caramel over cooked noodles with the salt and pepper, and continue stirring until thoroughly blended.
96bebe60-8842-4857-8b2b-2bc85ace5487 Let cool for a few minutes. Then add eggs one at a time, mixing after each addition.
96bebe60-8842-4857-8b2b-2bc85ace5487 Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in the preheated oven until nicely browned.
96bebe60-8842-4857-8b2b-2bc85ace5487 When done, remove immediately from pan. This kugel can be served hot, warm, or cold.
b74c70b0-8613-4373-974b-1fd699a662f3 Gather the ingredients.
b74c70b0-8613-4373-974b-1fd699a662f3 Preheat oven to 375 F. Spray a cookie sheet or shallow baking dish (9x13) with your favorite cooking spray. For easy cleanup, you can line your baking sheet or pan with aluminum foil and then spray with cooking spray to prevent sticking.
b74c70b0-8613-4373-974b-1fd699a662f3 Next, begin to slice and cut vegetables. There is no rule to follow here, but we prefer to slice the carrots, zucchini, squash, onions, and peppers. Potatoes are delicious in cubes or for small white potatoes, in quarters.
b74c70b0-8613-4373-974b-1fd699a662f3 After chopping and slicing, place vegetables in a single layer on a baking sheet or in ​​a dish. Drizzle with olive oil. Add the desired amount of salt and pepper. Sprinkle with garlic powder, thyme, and cumin.
b74c70b0-8613-4373-974b-1fd699a662f3 Place in heated over and cook for 45 minutes, or until vegetables can be pierced with a fork. Serve immediately.
b74c70b0-8613-4373-974b-1fd699a662f3 Enjoy!
441bca1a-1b0a-4338-a9e7-27a0ddaa2312 Rub the chicken breasts with the olive oil and grill for 5 to 6 minutes on each side until cooked all the way through. You can also do this on a grill pan on the stove top.
441bca1a-1b0a-4338-a9e7-27a0ddaa2312 While the chicken is grilling, make the sauce by adding the olive oil and diced onion to a saute pan. Saute on medium heat for about 10 minutes or until the onion is translucent. Stir in the tomato sauce, ground cumin, ground coriander, garlic powder, cinnamon, turmeric, cayenne, salt, and black pepper.
441bca1a-1b0a-4338-a9e7-27a0ddaa2312 Thinly slice or shred the cooked chicken breasts and add to the sauce. Simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
441bca1a-1b0a-4338-a9e7-27a0ddaa2312 Serve on small slider buns with sliced red onions or coleslaw.
a73f0230-4903-4f75-9c85-2a4158b01da3 Gather the ingredients.
a73f0230-4903-4f75-9c85-2a4158b01da3 Rinse the rice until the water runs clear. Drain in a colander and set aside.
a73f0230-4903-4f75-9c85-2a4158b01da3 In a medium saucepan, bring the 2 cups of water to a boil. Add the salt, stir, and then add the rinsed and drained rice. Stir with a fork.
a73f0230-4903-4f75-9c85-2a4158b01da3 Reduce the heat, cover the rice, and let it simmer for 20 minutes. Check it after 15 minutes to see if all the water has evaporated. If it has, the rice is ready. If not, replace the lid and let the rice simmer an additional 5 minutes.
a73f0230-4903-4f75-9c85-2a4158b01da3 Remove from the heat, fluff with a fork, and transfer into a serving dish.
8d3e8fe5-fca1-4942-9b2d-fee2058d3c4c Gather the ingredients.
8d3e8fe5-fca1-4942-9b2d-fee2058d3c4c Toast the pita bread in a pre-heated 400 F oven for about 5 minutes.
8d3e8fe5-fca1-4942-9b2d-fee2058d3c4c Then tear into 1-inch pieces.
c294b4db-b0ad-4ea0-b7ca-d6346909c937 Gather the ingredients.
c294b4db-b0ad-4ea0-b7ca-d6346909c937 Place the couscous in a dry sauté pan over medium heat and cook for 3 to 4 minutes, shaking the pan occasionally, until the couscous is lightly toasted.
c294b4db-b0ad-4ea0-b7ca-d6346909c937 Place the couscous in a saucepan, add 1 1/2 cups water and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to low and cover the pan. Cook for 8 to 9 minutes or until all the water has been absorbed and spoon it into a bowl.
c294b4db-b0ad-4ea0-b7ca-d6346909c937 While the couscous is cooking, toast the almonds in the sauté pan over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until they are lightly browned. Add to the couscous.
c294b4db-b0ad-4ea0-b7ca-d6346909c937 Stir in the cranberries and scallions, distributing them evenly.
c294b4db-b0ad-4ea0-b7ca-d6346909c937 Mix the olive oil, vinegar, and orange peel in a small bowl and pour over the couscous.
c294b4db-b0ad-4ea0-b7ca-d6346909c937 Toss the ingredients and season to taste with salt and pepper.
c294b4db-b0ad-4ea0-b7ca-d6346909c937 Enjoy!
02beea37-89cd-4e2f-8988-971c6dea802a Gather the ingredients.
02beea37-89cd-4e2f-8988-971c6dea802a Soak the bulghur wheat in cold water for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until soft.
02beea37-89cd-4e2f-8988-971c6dea802a While the bulghur wheat is soaking, prepare all the other ingredients. Chop the fresh parsley and the fresh mint, being sure to discard the stems.
02beea37-89cd-4e2f-8988-971c6dea802a Finely chop the medium onion and dice the tomatoes.
02beea37-89cd-4e2f-8988-971c6dea802a After soaking, squeeze out excess water from the bulghur wheat using your hands and/or a paper towel.
02beea37-89cd-4e2f-8988-971c6dea802a Combine all the ingredients in a bowl, except for the salt, pepper, lemon juice, and olive oil.
02beea37-89cd-4e2f-8988-971c6dea802a Line the serving bowl with grape leaves or romaine lettuce and add the mixed salad.
02beea37-89cd-4e2f-8988-971c6dea802a Sprinkle the olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper on top.
02beea37-89cd-4e2f-8988-971c6dea802a You can serve this immediately or, ideally, chill in the refrigerator for up to 2 hours before serving. This will give the flavors time to infuse.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Gather the ingredients.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Coat a large bowl with oil. Set aside.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 In a measuring cup, combine yeast, water, and sugar. Mix until yeast is dissolved. Set aside.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and salt.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Add yeast-water-sugar mixture and form a dough.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Knead dough for 10 to 15 minutes by hand or 5 to 8 minutes using a dough hook in a stand mixer.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Once the dough is kneaded, place the ball of dough in the oiled bowl. Roll the dough around the bowl to coat it with oil.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Cover and let rise for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until the dough doubles in size.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Once the dough has doubled, punch it down to release air.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Continue to knead for about 5 minutes.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Divide dough into 8 separate balls of dough.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Cover and allow to rise for 30 minutes.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Heat oven to 400 F.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Once the balls of dough have risen, roll them out into thin rectangles, about 12-by-10-inches for large lavash or 8-by-6-inches for small flatbreads. They should be as thin as pizza dough.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Transfer to parchment-lined baking sheets. Puncture the entire surface of the rectangles with the tines of a fork.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Brush dough with water and sprinkle with sesame seeds and poppy seeds if desired.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Remove from oven and eat while still warm or when cool.
5dc873fe-2d5e-43e1-9aa1-baca86eb6312 Enjoy!
6b5aac7c-9783-4128-b42c-79545bda135e Gather the ingredients.
6b5aac7c-9783-4128-b42c-79545bda135e First, heat the chopped onions in olive oil, butter or margarine stovetop in a large skillet. Allow the onions to cook, stirring occasionally, for about 5 to 7 minutes until they are softened.
6b5aac7c-9783-4128-b42c-79545bda135e Next, add the Israeli couscous to the skillet, and toast the grains, stirring, for just a minute or two, until they are lightly browned.
6b5aac7c-9783-4128-b42c-79545bda135e Once your Israeli couscous is lightly toasted, add about half of the vegetable broth and bring to a simmer. Allow to cook for about two to three minutes, stirring occasionally, then add in the other half of the vegetable broth. Allow to cook, stirring, for an additional 2 to 3 minutes.
6b5aac7c-9783-4128-b42c-79545bda135e Finally, add in the dry white wine, stirring to combine. Heat, stirring, for another 3 to 5 minutes, then add in the fresh spinach.
6b5aac7c-9783-4128-b42c-79545bda135e Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover, and allow to heat until spinach has wilted about 2 minutes, then turn off the heat and stir in the Parmesan cheese and season generously with sea salt or kosher salt and a bit of black pepper, to taste.
6b5aac7c-9783-4128-b42c-79545bda135e As soon as Parmesan cheese has melted, plate and serve immediately. Garnish individual servings with a bit of extra Parmesan cheese, if you'd like.
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 Gather the ingredients.
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 In a small saucepan, combine the cocoa powder and cold water, and whisk together until smooth.
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 Without putting over heat, add the sugar and torn mint leaves to the cocoa and water mixture.
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 Now place the saucepan over medium heat.
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 Bring the mixture to a boil, stirring constantly to melt the sugar. As soon as the syrup begins to boil, reduce the heat and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes. The mixture should begin to thicken in texture and have a glossy tint. Be careful as to not burn the mixture.
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 Once simmered to a thick consistency, remove from the heat and allow to cool.
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 When the syrup has cooled to near room temperature it is ready to be strained.
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 Use a fine mesh sieve to strain the syrup into a clean glass jar, carefully to remove any ingredients that may have clumped during the heating and cooling process. (If you do not have a sieve or want the authentic taste of an inconsistent texture, simply skip this process.)
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 Lastly, cover the jar and store in the refrigerator for up to three weeks. If the sugar starts to crystallize it may be time to make a new batch. To make it last simply reheat before using.
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 When ready to use drizzle over your favorite desserts, or make your traditional hot chocolate with a twist, or simply add to your baked goods for a minty surprise.
8f20fd53-d121-4d1d-a2ee-26e44811c2d2 Enjoy!
4f1c7f8b-a194-4a71-b1f4-c76ff527c3f5 In a food processor, combine beans, garlic, lemon juice, tahini (if desired) and yogurt. Blend well. Add salt, and blend until smooth and creamy.
4f1c7f8b-a194-4a71-b1f4-c76ff527c3f5 To thin the hummus (if desired), add a little of the chickpea liquid about a teaspoon at a time. You can also mix in warm water or olive oil to loosen the spread even more.
4dfbb922-e046-474e-b03f-8ade233a1fb8 Gather the ingredients.
4dfbb922-e046-474e-b03f-8ade233a1fb8 Coarsely chop the pulp and put it into a large pot along with enough water to cover the fruit. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce the heat and simmer until the fruit pulp is losing its color and flavor to the liquid, about 15 minutes.
4dfbb922-e046-474e-b03f-8ade233a1fb8 Strain the liquid through a jelly bag, several layers of cheesecloth in a colander, or a cloth produce bag.
4dfbb922-e046-474e-b03f-8ade233a1fb8 Measure the strained liquid. You should have about 4 cups. Return the prickly pear liquid to the pot (wash the pot first if there are any seeds sticking to it).
4dfbb922-e046-474e-b03f-8ade233a1fb8 Add the sugar and lemon juice. Bring the mixture to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring to dissolve the sugar.
4dfbb922-e046-474e-b03f-8ade233a1fb8 A foamy scum usually forms on the surface of the prickly pear syrup while it is coming to a boil. Skim as much of this off as possible and discard it.
4dfbb922-e046-474e-b03f-8ade233a1fb8 Pour the still-hot prickly pear syrup into clean pint or half-pint canning jars (it is not necessary to sterilize the jars for this recipe). Be sure to leave half an inch of headspace between the surface of the syrup and the rims of the jars. Wipe the rims of the jars clean with a damp paper towel or a clean dishcloth.​
4dfbb922-e046-474e-b03f-8ade233a1fb8 Screw on canning lids and process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes (adjust the canning time if you live at a high altitude). Alternatively, skip the canning process and refrigerate your prickly pear syrup for up to 1 month.
0074c8c4-8618-4103-8dd9-dc827194ab26 Place the colander over a large bowl. Line the colander with the cheesecloth, muslin bag, or paper coffee filters. Spoon in the yogurt.
0074c8c4-8618-4103-8dd9-dc827194ab26 Leave the yogurt to drain for 24 hours, refrigerated for a milder flavor or at room temperature for a tangier labneh.
0074c8c4-8618-4103-8dd9-dc827194ab26 The liquid that separates out into the bowl is whey. You can use it to kickstart lacto-fermented pickles, especially if you want to reduce or eliminate the amount of salt in them. Whey will keep in the refrigerator for up to a month.
0074c8c4-8618-4103-8dd9-dc827194ab26 Mix the salt, pepper, and herbs (if using) into the yogurt.
0074c8c4-8618-4103-8dd9-dc827194ab26 Spoon the labneh as is into jars or containers and store it in the refrigerator for up to 1 week. For longer storage, use the traditional oil-preserved method below.
0074c8c4-8618-4103-8dd9-dc827194ab26 Lightly coat your hands with olive oil. Scoop up a scant tablespoon of labneh and gently shape it into a ball. The labneh will be soft, but you should still be able to shape it into a ball that holds together.
0074c8c4-8618-4103-8dd9-dc827194ab26 Place the labneh balls carefully into clean, dry glass jars. Pour the extra-virgin olive oil over the labneh. For decoration and extra flavor, you can tuck in a few sprigs of fresh herbs as you add the labneh and oil.
0074c8c4-8618-4103-8dd9-dc827194ab26 Lightly tap the jars on the side to release any air bubbles. Cover and store in the refrigerator for up to 2 months.
c4257284-0e9e-465f-a24f-94290a124ec8 Preheat oven to 375 F.
c4257284-0e9e-465f-a24f-94290a124ec8 In a large mixing bowl, combine the yeast, nigella seeds, and baking powder. Stir until well mixed. Add in the flour and repeat mixing until all ingredients are well combined.
c4257284-0e9e-465f-a24f-94290a124ec8 Set aside and warm the cup of milk in a small saucepan until lukewarm only. It should be close to room temperature. It is not important to be exact, just so long as the milk is not specifically hot or cold.
c4257284-0e9e-465f-a24f-94290a124ec8 Then, in a separate small mixing bowl place the egg, yogurt, milk, and melted ghee. Once combined, pour into the spice and flour mixture.
c4257284-0e9e-465f-a24f-94290a124ec8 Mix together until a ball of dough forms. Knead the dough until it is elastic enough to build loaves with. Separate the dough into 8 equal parts.
c4257284-0e9e-465f-a24f-94290a124ec8 Create oval shapes with the dough and flatten until about 1/2 inch thick.
c4257284-0e9e-465f-a24f-94290a124ec8 Place 2 to 3 on a baking sheet at a time. Place in the oven for 15 minutes on the middle rack. If the top does not appear brown at this time, place the baking sheet on the top rack for 2 minutes.
c4257284-0e9e-465f-a24f-94290a124ec8 Remove from the oven and drizzle lightly with olive oil. Sprinkle a pinch of Za'atar on each loaf and place in a bread basket to keep warm. Repeat the cooking process with the additional uncooked loaves.
c4257284-0e9e-465f-a24f-94290a124ec8 Once all loaves are cooked serve with fresh hummus or Taziki.
6f4b8d47-9407-4cc8-a3f2-36b8d2bd5c69 Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
6f4b8d47-9407-4cc8-a3f2-36b8d2bd5c69 Add the green beans and cook until bright green and crisp-tender, about 3 to 4 minutes.
6f4b8d47-9407-4cc8-a3f2-36b8d2bd5c69 Drain and set aside.
6f4b8d47-9407-4cc8-a3f2-36b8d2bd5c69 In a chef's pan or large skillet, warm the olive oil over medium-high heat.
6f4b8d47-9407-4cc8-a3f2-36b8d2bd5c69 Add the garlic and sauté until fragrant, about 30 to 60 seconds.
6f4b8d47-9407-4cc8-a3f2-36b8d2bd5c69 Add the green beans and pecans and sauté to coat with the oil.
6f4b8d47-9407-4cc8-a3f2-36b8d2bd5c69 Drizzle with the date syrup, toss together quickly, and remove from the heat.
6f4b8d47-9407-4cc8-a3f2-36b8d2bd5c69 Transfer to a serving platter or bowl.
6f4b8d47-9407-4cc8-a3f2-36b8d2bd5c69 Drizzle with additional date syrup if desired.
6f4b8d47-9407-4cc8-a3f2-36b8d2bd5c69 Serve warm or at room temperature. Enjoy!
29b69b8c-55a4-4386-93a8-b19bf3b1b5b5 Rinse the rice in a fine mesh colander until the water runs clear. Drain well.
29b69b8c-55a4-4386-93a8-b19bf3b1b5b5 Warm the oil in a heavy-bottomed saucepan, set over medium-high heat. Stir in the rice, turmeric, and curry powder, mixing well to coat the rice with the spices and oil. Add the raisins, vegetable stock and soy sauce and bring to a boil.
29b69b8c-55a4-4386-93a8-b19bf3b1b5b5 Reduce the heat to low, cover the pot, and simmer for 18 minutes. (Do not lift the lid while cooking or the rice will become sticky.)
29b69b8c-55a4-4386-93a8-b19bf3b1b5b5 Remove the rice from the heat, stir to fluff, then replace the cover and allow the rice to rest for 10 minutes.
29b69b8c-55a4-4386-93a8-b19bf3b1b5b5 Mound the rice onto a platter and serve. Enjoy!
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 Gather the ingredients.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 Preheat the oven to 400 F.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 Slice each acorn squash in half, lengthwise, and scoop out the seeds. You should have four boat-shaped pieces. Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and roast in the oven for 20 minutes or until the squash is fork tender. Set aside.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 Spread the bread cubes out on the baking sheet. Bake in the oven for about 10 minutes or until the cubes are a lightly toasted.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 Add two tablespoons of the butter to a large skillet or cast iron pan. Add the diced onion and, on medium heat, saute for about 10 minutes until translucent.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 While the onion is sauteing, add the chicken stock and the remaining 6 tablespoons of butter to a pot and heat, allowing the butter to melt.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 Scoop the cooked flesh out of the acorn squash, but leave enough in the skin to use as a bowl.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 Add the squash and toasted bread cubes to a large bowl.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 Stir in the cooked onion and ladle in the warm chicken and butter stock. Fluff with a fork to combine and make sure the bread absorbs the liquid.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 Stir in the rosemary, thyme, sage, parsley and slivered almonds. Season with the za'atar, salt, and pepper.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 Scoop the stuffing into each of the hollowed out acorn squash shells and either refrigerate until ready to use or return to the oven for about 15 minutes for the flavors to meld together and the stuffing to heat through.
373c5c70-1785-4bb1-9611-c15a18d1d345 You can also forgo the squash bowls and just scoop into a large casserole dish or individual ramekins.
6b4bf9f6-c48a-4e46-be4a-a6fd1ed97bb0 In a medium sauce pot, bring chicken broth, lemon juice, and lemon zest to a boil.
6b4bf9f6-c48a-4e46-be4a-a6fd1ed97bb0 In a medium bowl, combine couscous and salt.
6b4bf9f6-c48a-4e46-be4a-a6fd1ed97bb0 Pour boiling broth over couscous and allow to sit, covered for 10 minutes, or until the broth is absorbed.
6b4bf9f6-c48a-4e46-be4a-a6fd1ed97bb0 Fluff couscous with a fork and serve immediately.
fdbb3e14-6c4e-4c6d-9ab5-cbc392f1085c Wash and spin dry the spinach leaves and layer them on a serving platter.
fdbb3e14-6c4e-4c6d-9ab5-cbc392f1085c Peel the blood orange and cut into slices approximately 1/4" thick. Layer the orange slices over the spinach.
fdbb3e14-6c4e-4c6d-9ab5-cbc392f1085c Sprinkle the crumbled feta cheese over the salad.
fdbb3e14-6c4e-4c6d-9ab5-cbc392f1085c Whisk together the olive oil, blood orange juice, ground sumac, salt and pepper and drizzle over the salad.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Gather the ingredients.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 In large bowl, mix together yeast, water, sugar, and salt.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Stir in vegetable oil and eggs.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Mix in enough bread flour to make a thick dough that can be kneaded by hand.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Turn dough out onto board and knead for 8 minutes.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Put dough in greased bowl and turn dough over in the bowl so that the top is also lightly greased. Cover with clean kitchen towel and let rise for 1 hour in a warm, draft-free place.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Punch down.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Turn dough out onto lightly floured board and knead out bubbles for 5 minutes.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Divide dough into 6 equal pieces. Set 3 pieces aside.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Roll out the remaining 3 pieces of dough between your hands, making 3 strips, about 11- to 12-inches long.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Line strips side-by-side on floured board and pinch the top ends together.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Braid strips and pinch bottom ends together.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Set braided loaf on greased baking sheet and repeat steps for the remaining 3 pieces of dough.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Cover loaves with kitchen towel and let rise in a warm, draft-free place for 30 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Uncover bread and brush on egg yolk. Sprinkle with poppy seeds.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Bake at 400 F for 40 minutes or until bread sounds hollow when tapped on.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Let bread cool on rack.
eab209e0-0c0a-403c-afbd-c71274188dd8 Serve warm.
eca70058-cc22-4f7f-b975-d55c7715c0be Soak grape leaves in cold water for 2 to 3 hours. Jarred grape leaves are very salty from the brine solution.
eca70058-cc22-4f7f-b975-d55c7715c0be Rinse and drain in a colander. Set aside.
eca70058-cc22-4f7f-b975-d55c7715c0be In a mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Mix well with hands.
eca70058-cc22-4f7f-b975-d55c7715c0be Place a grape leaf side down. Place about 1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture in the middle.
eca70058-cc22-4f7f-b975-d55c7715c0be Fold in the sides and roll upward. Think of rolling a burrito, only smaller.
eca70058-cc22-4f7f-b975-d55c7715c0be When you have rolled the last leaf, place a heavy plate on top of the stuffed grape leaves in your pan. We use a ceramic plate. This helps keep the grape leaves in place during cooking so they don't shift around.
eca70058-cc22-4f7f-b975-d55c7715c0be Fill pan with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for about 30 to 45 minutes until rice and meat are done.
f516ad06-7e3e-4a5c-ac1c-f0102b87e816 Gather the ingredients.
f516ad06-7e3e-4a5c-ac1c-f0102b87e816 Slice the eggplant in half.
f516ad06-7e3e-4a5c-ac1c-f0102b87e816 On a baking sheet, roast the eggplant in a 400 F oven for approximately 45 minutes, or until soft.
f516ad06-7e3e-4a5c-ac1c-f0102b87e816 Remove the eggplant from the oven and allow it to cool slightly, then scoop out inside of eggplant, leaving skin behind.
f516ad06-7e3e-4a5c-ac1c-f0102b87e816 In a blender or food processor, combine eggplant, chickpeas, garlic, lemon juice, tahini, and sea salt until smooth. The mixture will be somewhat thick. Slowly incorporate the olive oil until well mixed.
f516ad06-7e3e-4a5c-ac1c-f0102b87e816 Mix in the optional fresh chopped parsley by hand.
f516ad06-7e3e-4a5c-ac1c-f0102b87e816 Enjoy your homemade baba ghanoush hummus served with veggies, pita (or any other kind of flatbread), or as a sandwich spread. To serve, drizzle with a little bit of extra olive oil (use the best quality you have) and sprinkle with chili powder, paprika or cumin for a bit of color. Spread some baba ghanoush in a flour tortilla and add lettuce, tomatoes, and veggies for a vegan sandwich wrap.
c60bb669-17e6-453b-aec2-03c4e5c5ee2d Gather the ingredients.
c60bb669-17e6-453b-aec2-03c4e5c5ee2d In a large bowl, toss together the chopped tomatoes, cucumbers, pepper, and scallions.
c60bb669-17e6-453b-aec2-03c4e5c5ee2d Immediately before serving, season with olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Toss well, taste, and adjust the seasonings if desired.
c60bb669-17e6-453b-aec2-03c4e5c5ee2d Leftover salad will keep, covered in the refrigerator, for 2 to 3 days.
27e58bb7-7f83-4551-ae12-cc48a4331f0b Drain chickpeas and rinse thoroughly and set aside.
27e58bb7-7f83-4551-ae12-cc48a4331f0b In a large saucepan, sauté onion and garlic in olive oil until soft and a light golden color.
27e58bb7-7f83-4551-ae12-cc48a4331f0b Add chicken stock or broth and bring to a boil.
27e58bb7-7f83-4551-ae12-cc48a4331f0b Stir in uncooked rice, drained chickpeas, salt, and pepper. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer on low heat for twenty minutes.
27e58bb7-7f83-4551-ae12-cc48a4331f0b After twenty minutes, remove from heat and let sit, covered, for 3 to 5 minutes.
27e58bb7-7f83-4551-ae12-cc48a4331f0b Remove lid and fluff with a fork. Serve immediately.
1a266235-75ff-45e0-a09a-50cad54579e1 Rinse the chickpeas and drain well to remove all the excess liquid. Place in a large bowl.
1a266235-75ff-45e0-a09a-50cad54579e1 Cut the stem end off each Brussels sprout and then slice in half. Place in a food processor and pulse a few times until shredded but not pureed. Add to the chickpeas.
1a266235-75ff-45e0-a09a-50cad54579e1 Make the lemon tahini dressing by combining the sesame paste with the water and lemon juice. Grate in the garlic, using a fine grater, and season with salt and pepper to taste. If you'd like a slightly thinner consistency, add an additional tablespoon of water.
1a266235-75ff-45e0-a09a-50cad54579e1 Toss the chickpeas and Brussels sprouts with half of the lemon tahini dressing (or more as desired) and the za'atar.
a8401f80-e838-4eb2-8131-cdf47b4e3c7c Gather the ingredients.
a8401f80-e838-4eb2-8131-cdf47b4e3c7c Finely chop tomatoes, cucumbers, and onions.
a8401f80-e838-4eb2-8131-cdf47b4e3c7c Toss with remaining ingredients and gently mix well.
a8401f80-e838-4eb2-8131-cdf47b4e3c7c Serve chilled.
69f1b537-a288-4f86-b63a-71898936d6de Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Shell the peas and add them to the boiling water, reduce the heat to medium and cook for about 5 minutes. Drain and set aside.
69f1b537-a288-4f86-b63a-71898936d6de Add the olive oil and minced garlic to a large saute pan or skillet. Saute for about a minute, just until the garlic is translucent but be careful not to burn it.
69f1b537-a288-4f86-b63a-71898936d6de Add the cooked peas and toss to coat and warm the peas. Season with the sumac, salt, and pepper.
69f1b537-a288-4f86-b63a-71898936d6de Serve warm with the crumbled feta cheese on top.
336af1fe-f503-45ca-a4e1-846638ec4297 Gather the ingredients.
336af1fe-f503-45ca-a4e1-846638ec4297 ﻿Rinse and dry the arugula or spinach and place on a large serving plate or board. Slice the cherry tomatoes into halves or quarters, depending on size. Leave some just sliced in half on the side for dipping into the hummus. Arrange the remaining tomato slices on top of the greens.
336af1fe-f503-45ca-a4e1-846638ec4297 Rinse and dry the chickpeas and spread them out over the greens.
336af1fe-f503-45ca-a4e1-846638ec4297 Wash and thinly slice the cucumber. If you're using an English (seedless) cucumber, there's no need to peel or seed. Arrange the slices on the salad but leave a few in a pile on the side for dipping into hummus.
336af1fe-f503-45ca-a4e1-846638ec4297 Sprinkle the sumac over the salad and season with salt and pepper.
336af1fe-f503-45ca-a4e1-846638ec4297 Add the hummus to a bowl on the side of the platter along with the warmed pita rounds. Drizzle the salad with some of the tahini dressing but leave the rest in a bowl on the side for people to add more if they like.
7b008745-356a-4114-a282-24e3f9a46913 If you buy store bought stuffing bread cubes they should already be toasted. But if you're using homemade, spread the cubes out on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake in a 400 F oven for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly golden bread. The toasted bread will absorb the liquid better.
7b008745-356a-4114-a282-24e3f9a46913 Add 2 tablespoons of butter to a large skillet or cast iron pan along with the onion. Sauté on medium heat for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the onions are translucent or a light golden brown.
7b008745-356a-4114-a282-24e3f9a46913 Stir in the almonds and apples and continue sautéing and stirring for another 5 to 10 minutes. Stir in the parsley and thyme.
7b008745-356a-4114-a282-24e3f9a46913 While the onion is sautéing, add the chicken stock (you can use vegetable stock if you prefer) and cardamom to a pot and simmer.
7b008745-356a-4114-a282-24e3f9a46913 Add the toasted bread cubes to a large bowl. Stir in the sautéed onion mixture and pour on the warm stock. Stir to combine and to make sure the bread is absorbing the liquid but try not to mash it too much.
7b008745-356a-4114-a282-24e3f9a46913 Fluff a bit with a fork and transfer to a baking dish.
7b008745-356a-4114-a282-24e3f9a46913 When ready to serve, bake in a 350 F oven for 20 minutes.
fd995499-4cdf-4ed5-8cba-581bb267354a Gather the ingredients.
fd995499-4cdf-4ed5-8cba-581bb267354a Pre-heat the oven to 400 degrees.
fd995499-4cdf-4ed5-8cba-581bb267354a Slice the heirloom tomatoes and place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Drizzle with two tablespoons of olive oil and sprinkle with the za'atar. Roast in the oven for approximately 30 minutes or until the tomatoes are starting to get a little color but not burned.
fd995499-4cdf-4ed5-8cba-581bb267354a Brush the slices of Italian bread with the remaining tablespoon of olive oil and grill or toast in the oven for approximately 10 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
fd995499-4cdf-4ed5-8cba-581bb267354a Spread each slice with the softened feta cheese and top with the roasted heirloom tomatoes. Cut each slice in half and serve warm as an appetizer with a cocktail or glass of wine.
5a93c2d4-0504-4636-8eb0-55c9993328d2 Add the pasta to a large pot of boiling salted water and cook according to the package directions. Drain the cooked pasta and return to the pot. Stir in the rinsed and drained chickpeas as well as the baby spinach leaves. Note that the residual heat of the pasta will cook the spinach down a bit.
5a93c2d4-0504-4636-8eb0-55c9993328d2 Make the dressing by whisking together the chopped garlic scapes or minced garlic, olive oil, fresh lemon juice, sesame paste, water, red pepper flakes, dried oregano, ground black pepper and salt.
5a93c2d4-0504-4636-8eb0-55c9993328d2 Toss the pasta, spinach and chickpeas with the dressing and serve at room temperature.
a4a97c08-6117-4a4f-af93-8bd22a65383b Gather the ingredients.
a4a97c08-6117-4a4f-af93-8bd22a65383b You can grate the shallot, potato, and squash by hand on a box grater but it's easier to use the grating attachment on a food processor. Begin with the shallot, then the squash and then the potato.
a4a97c08-6117-4a4f-af93-8bd22a65383b Transfer the grated vegetables to a large bowl and mix in the egg, flour, salt, za'atar and pepper.
a4a97c08-6117-4a4f-af93-8bd22a65383b Heat the canola oil in a large skillet or cast iron pan.
a4a97c08-6117-4a4f-af93-8bd22a65383b Drop spoonfuls of the batter into the pan. I made mine about 3 inches but you can make them smaller or larger. Fry on medium heat for about 5 to 7 minutes on each side or until the pancakes are a light golden brown. Repeat until you've used all the batter.
a4a97c08-6117-4a4f-af93-8bd22a65383b Top with a dollop of labneh and an additional sprinkling of za'atar.
a4a97c08-6117-4a4f-af93-8bd22a65383b Serve and enjoy!
b1f28883-8a78-4409-b3c8-616b546e5c72 Make the tahini sauce by combining the garlic, sesame paste, lemon juice, Greek yogurt and water in the bowl of a small food processor. Puree until fully combined and season with salt and pepper.
b1f28883-8a78-4409-b3c8-616b546e5c72 Remove the skin from the chicken and shred or dice the meat.
b1f28883-8a78-4409-b3c8-616b546e5c72 Add the chicken to a large bowl along with the shredded carrots and toss with the tahini sauce.
b1f28883-8a78-4409-b3c8-616b546e5c72 Stir in the sliced almonds, chopped cilantro and za'atar.
b1f28883-8a78-4409-b3c8-616b546e5c72 Season with additional salt and pepper as desired.
b1f28883-8a78-4409-b3c8-616b546e5c72 Serve on pita or naan bread with greens such as baby spinach.
acb454e5-1ffd-475c-bd8b-38cfc1ca2dfc Gather the ingredients.
acb454e5-1ffd-475c-bd8b-38cfc1ca2dfc Add the olive oil and diced onion to a large skillet.
acb454e5-1ffd-475c-bd8b-38cfc1ca2dfc Saute over medium low heat for a few minutes, until the onions become translucent.
acb454e5-1ffd-475c-bd8b-38cfc1ca2dfc Peel the butternut squash and cut in half with a sharp knife.
acb454e5-1ffd-475c-bd8b-38cfc1ca2dfc Scoop out the seeds with a spoon and then cut the squash into small chunks.
acb454e5-1ffd-475c-bd8b-38cfc1ca2dfc Working in batches, add a few of the chunks to a food processor and pulse a few times until you get a rice-like size and consistency.
acb454e5-1ffd-475c-bd8b-38cfc1ca2dfc Add the riced butternut squash to the pan with the onion and continue sauteing for a few minutes until the squash softens a bit but doesn't become mushy.
acb454e5-1ffd-475c-bd8b-38cfc1ca2dfc Season with the garlic powder, cumin, salt and pepper.
acb454e5-1ffd-475c-bd8b-38cfc1ca2dfc Stir in the parsley and top with the slivered almonds.
acb454e5-1ffd-475c-bd8b-38cfc1ca2dfc Serve and enjoy!
e0cf6311-bb42-42b4-aaa0-aa247baecf00 Gather the ingredients.
e0cf6311-bb42-42b4-aaa0-aa247baecf00 ﻿In a medium bowl, whisk together the eggs and canola oil.
e0cf6311-bb42-42b4-aaa0-aa247baecf00 Stir in the matzo meal, salt, za'atar and baking powder until well combined and then stir in the water. Note that the mixture will be very loose but will thicken as it stands. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
e0cf6311-bb42-42b4-aaa0-aa247baecf00 Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Scoop approximately 1 ounce ball of the matzo batter into the water. Cover, reduce the heat to low and let simmer for 30 minutes.
e0cf6311-bb42-42b4-aaa0-aa247baecf00 Remove the cooked matzo balls with a slotted spoon or spider strainer and add to soup.
e0cf6311-bb42-42b4-aaa0-aa247baecf00 Serve and enjoy!
f8940d00-5809-4eaf-985b-5f5b3a41070f Gather the ingredients.
f8940d00-5809-4eaf-985b-5f5b3a41070f Trim the ends of the green beans and add to a pot of boiling water. Cook on high heat for approximately 10 minutes or until the beans are fork tender. Drain.
f8940d00-5809-4eaf-985b-5f5b3a41070f While the beans are cooking, Add 2 tablespoons of the olive oil to a skillet or cast iron pan along with the peeled and sliced onions. Saute for about 10 minutes until the onions are lightly caramelized.
f8940d00-5809-4eaf-985b-5f5b3a41070f When the onions are done, remove from the pan and add to the cooked and drained green beans. Add the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil to the pan along with the breadcrumbs and za'atar. Saute for about 2 minutes, stirring often, until lightly browned.
f8940d00-5809-4eaf-985b-5f5b3a41070f Toss the green beans and onions with the breadcrumbs and season with salt and pepper to taste.
f0847036-92aa-41bf-b3eb-321776fbab59 Gather the ingredients.
f0847036-92aa-41bf-b3eb-321776fbab59 Wash the radishes. Slice off the stem ends and tips. If using watermelon or daikon radishes, peel them. Leave cherry belle and other rosy-skinned radishes unpeeled.
f0847036-92aa-41bf-b3eb-321776fbab59 Slice the radishes into 1/8-inch-thick rounds. Smaller radishes simply can be cut in half and very small ones (less than 1 inch in diameter) can be left whole.
f0847036-92aa-41bf-b3eb-321776fbab59 Divide the dill, garlic, bay leaves, mustard seeds, cumin seeds, and optional pepper flakes evenly between two glass pint jars. It is not necessary to sterilize the jars for this recipe but they should be scrupulously clean.
f0847036-92aa-41bf-b3eb-321776fbab59 Pack the radishes in with the spices.
f0847036-92aa-41bf-b3eb-321776fbab59 To make the brine, bring the water, vinegar, honey, and salt to boil in a small saucepan, stirring to dissolve the honey and salt.
f0847036-92aa-41bf-b3eb-321776fbab59 Skim off any foam and discard.
f0847036-92aa-41bf-b3eb-321776fbab59 Pour the hot brine over the radishes and seasonings. The radishes should be completely immersed in the brine.
f0847036-92aa-41bf-b3eb-321776fbab59 Tightly cover and store in the refrigerator. Pickled radishes will be ready to eat in 24 hours but will be even better if you can wait a week before serving them.
f0847036-92aa-41bf-b3eb-321776fbab59 Serve pickled radishes as a condiment or chop them and add to grain-based salads like tabbouleh.
b752f7ba-9a16-48a4-b699-8aee7a1f5d82 Gather the ingredients.
b752f7ba-9a16-48a4-b699-8aee7a1f5d82 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
b752f7ba-9a16-48a4-b699-8aee7a1f5d82 Add the feta cheese, cream cheese, za'atar, and dried oregano to a food processor along with one tablespoon of the milk. Puree until smooth, adding an additional tablespoon of milk if needed to get a creamy texture. Note that the mixture will be quite salty but it will also provide the seasoning for the pastry and tomatoes.
b752f7ba-9a16-48a4-b699-8aee7a1f5d82 Gently brush a layer of fillo pastry with the melted butter or olive oil, top with another layer and repeat until all the layers are done.
b752f7ba-9a16-48a4-b699-8aee7a1f5d82 Spread the feta cheese mixture over the top layer of fillo, leaving about a 1 1/2 inch border on all sides.
b752f7ba-9a16-48a4-b699-8aee7a1f5d82 Slice or quarter the tomatoes, depending on their size and spread on top of the feta cheese mixture. Fold up the sides of the filo to create a rectangular tart with an edge. Make sure to brush any exposed dough with some of the melted butter or olive oil.
b752f7ba-9a16-48a4-b699-8aee7a1f5d82 Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 45 minutes or until the pastry is a light golden brown. Finish by topping with the chopped fresh parsley.
b752f7ba-9a16-48a4-b699-8aee7a1f5d82 Serve and enjoy!
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Gather the ingredients.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Set up the boiling water bath that you will process your jars of asparagus pickles in, and turn the heat on high to bring the water to a boil.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Wash the asparagus. Hold each spear at either end and bend it until it snaps. From the point at which it snapped to the pointy tip of the spear is the tender portion that you will pickle.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c If necessary, trim the bottom ends of the tender asparagus spears so that none of them is longer than 6 inches.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Slice off the ends of the onion and peel it. Cut the onion in half lengthwise and then slice the halves into slivers.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Peel and smash the garlic.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Pierce fresh chile peppers with the tip of a knife, or break dried chile peppers in half.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Combine the vinegar, water, sugar or honey, salt, and spices in a medium pot. Bring to a boil over high heat.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes to release the flavors of the spices.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c While the vinegar and spice brine is simmering, load the jars. Divide the onion slivers, hot peppers and garlic between two quart-sized canning jars. It is not necessary to sterilize the jars for this recipe, but they should be scrupulously clean.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Place one of the jars on its side (it's easier to tightly load in the asparagus spears that way). Lay the asparagus in with the pointy tip end facing the rim of the jar. Keep adding more spears until it is impossible to fit in even one more: the asparagus will shrink a little during canning, and packing the spears in tightly keeps them from floating up out of the brine.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Repeat with the other jar.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Pour the hot brine over the asparagus spears. They should be completely covered by the liquid but still have at least 1/2-inch of space between the surface of the brine and the rims of the jars.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Screw on canning lids and process in the boiling water bath for 20 minutes.
4b7fdfb0-8513-42bd-a29d-a5ef982ba94c Wait at least a week before tasting. It takes that long for the flavors to combine and mellow.
0595bd92-a750-41df-b206-559ebd9ed752 In a large pot, cover the lentils with an ample amount of water and bring to a boil. Add salt and pepper. Once the lentils have boiled, reduce heat to a simmer and let sit for 45 minutes.
0595bd92-a750-41df-b206-559ebd9ed752 About 15 minutes before the lentils being done, saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons of olive oil until soft. Keep on low until lentils are finished cooking.
0595bd92-a750-41df-b206-559ebd9ed752 Once lentils are done, drain excess water and allow to sit uncovered for 5 minutes to cool.
0595bd92-a750-41df-b206-559ebd9ed752 Add onions and garlic and combine well. Be careful not to crush the lentils!
0595bd92-a750-41df-b206-559ebd9ed752 Add olive oil, lemon juice, and parsley. Serve immediately or allow to chill and serve. Great the next day also!
87bf6d10-e120-4724-a2fc-73e70bbba868 Gather the ingredients.
87bf6d10-e120-4724-a2fc-73e70bbba868 Preheat the oven to 400 F.
87bf6d10-e120-4724-a2fc-73e70bbba868 Wrap the beets tightly in aluminum foil, place on a baking sheet to catch any drips and roast in the oven for 45 minutes to an hour or until the beets can be easily pierced with the tip of a knife. Remove from the oven and allow to cool enough to be handled. Peel the beets (the peel will come off easily with a paring knife) and dice.
87bf6d10-e120-4724-a2fc-73e70bbba868 Make the dressing by whisking together the olive oil, lemon juice, mayonnaise or mustard (to help emulsify the dressing), honey and sumac in a bowl. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
87bf6d10-e120-4724-a2fc-73e70bbba868 To assemble the salads, divide the salad greens evenly on four plates, top with an equal amount of sliced red onions, diced beets, and crumbled goat cheese.
87bf6d10-e120-4724-a2fc-73e70bbba868 Drizzle with the dressing and serve with slices of pita bread.
87bf6d10-e120-4724-a2fc-73e70bbba868 Enjoy!
bf412ed0-67cd-442b-a450-2ac813e51542 Gather the ingredients.
bf412ed0-67cd-442b-a450-2ac813e51542 Preheat the oven to 400 F.
bf412ed0-67cd-442b-a450-2ac813e51542 Split the squash in half lengthwise, scoop out the seeds, and rub with 1 tablespoon of the olive oil.
bf412ed0-67cd-442b-a450-2ac813e51542 Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and roast for 45 minutes or until the squash is tender.
bf412ed0-67cd-442b-a450-2ac813e51542 Toss the chickpeas with the remaining tablespoon of olive oil.
bf412ed0-67cd-442b-a450-2ac813e51542 When the squash has cooked for 25 minutes, add the chickpeas to the baking sheet for the remaining 20 minutes.
bf412ed0-67cd-442b-a450-2ac813e51542 Make the tahini sauce by adding the garlic clove, sesame paste, Greek yogurt, lemon juice and water to a small food processor. Puree until completely smooth and season with salt and black pepper to taste. If you'd like the dressing a little thinner, continue adding water, 1 teaspoon at a time, until you have the desired consistency.
bf412ed0-67cd-442b-a450-2ac813e51542 Serve each half of the roasted squash with half the chickpeas. Sprinkle with the za'atar and drizzle on the Greek yogurt tahini sauce. Serve over a bed of baby spinach or cooked rice.
f006810f-ad1d-4a6c-b0a7-c4f9fb12745b In a medium saucepan, combine the pumpkin puree (be sure to use plain pumpkin and not pumpkin pie filling), clove, cinnamon, ginger, allspice, sugar, lemon juice, salt, and vanilla extract on medium-high heat, stirring constantly. Bring the mixture to a boil and then reduce the heat to low. Allow the mixture to simmer for about 45 to 60 minutes. Check and stir frequently to prevent it from sticking to the bottom of the pan. If this occurs, lower the heat even further. When making jams and jellies, it is best to use a non-stick pan instead of stainless steel or copper bottom pans to avoid a reaction with the metals.
f006810f-ad1d-4a6c-b0a7-c4f9fb12745b After 45 to 60 minutes, the mixture will be thick and a clear orange color―almost translucent. Taste the jam to see if it needs any additional salt. Then pour it into sterilized jars and seal once cooled. Note that if you are not preserving, you can also place the jam in unsterilized containers and store in the refrigerator but be sure to use within a week or two.
f006810f-ad1d-4a6c-b0a7-c4f9fb12745b If you are a first-time canner, it is important that you follow canning safety procedures very carefully. If not, you may put yourself or others at risk of food poisoning and also risking premature spoilage.
f006810f-ad1d-4a6c-b0a7-c4f9fb12745b Note that if using fresh pumpkin, choose one that is anywhere from 2 to 3 lbs. and roast for an hour in a 400 F oven until tender. Scoop out the seeds and then spoon the flesh into the pot as you would with canned pumpkin puree.
f006810f-ad1d-4a6c-b0a7-c4f9fb12745b For some fun variations, try substituting pure maple syrup for some of the granulated sugar for a more autumnal flavor.
fae78090-0fb2-44cf-b11d-3537b314da77 Add the potatoes to a large pot of salted boiling water and cook for about 10 minutes or until just fork tender.
fae78090-0fb2-44cf-b11d-3537b314da77 If you're using the small potatoes, there's no need to peel them. Or you can choose to peel them after they've cooked and cooled as the peel will come off easier then.
fae78090-0fb2-44cf-b11d-3537b314da77 Drain the potatoes and slice in half or quarters depending on the size.
fae78090-0fb2-44cf-b11d-3537b314da77 Add the two tablespoons of olive oil and minced garlic to a cast iron pan and saute for a minute, just until the garlic is slightly translucent. Do not allow the garlic to burn or it will become bitter.
fae78090-0fb2-44cf-b11d-3537b314da77 Add the cooked potatoes to the pan and stir to coat them in the olive oil and garlic.
fae78090-0fb2-44cf-b11d-3537b314da77 Saute on medium heat for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
fae78090-0fb2-44cf-b11d-3537b314da77 Stir in the chili paste and continue sauteing for an additional 15 minutes.
fae78090-0fb2-44cf-b11d-3537b314da77 Stir in the cilantro and season with additional salt, if needed.
190482e1-e3c2-44f7-8a6b-5b9f2096827b To make a basic Greek yogurt style tahini sauce, add the garlic clove, sesame paste, Greek yogurt, lemon juice, and water to a small food processor and puree until smooth.
190482e1-e3c2-44f7-8a6b-5b9f2096827b Season with salt and pepper to taste. If you'd like the dressing a little thinner, continue adding water, 1 teaspoon at a time, until you have the desired consistency.
190482e1-e3c2-44f7-8a6b-5b9f2096827b To make a cilantro version, add 1 to 2 teaspoons of chopped cilantro to the food processor.
1d52e468-b396-43cf-8ab7-5ca5603e6f19 Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.
1d52e468-b396-43cf-8ab7-5ca5603e6f19 Add the beet, chickpeas, garlic, tahini sauce, flour, parsley and cumin to a food processor. Pulse until the mixture comes together but it doesn't need to be a smooth paste. Season with salt and pepper.
1d52e468-b396-43cf-8ab7-5ca5603e6f19 Form 1 oz. balls (use can use a scoop) and place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Bake for 30 minutes.
1d52e468-b396-43cf-8ab7-5ca5603e6f19 Serve over greens, drizzled with tahini sauce. You can also serve this in a pita with salad or over pasta instead of meatballs.
4ff277a7-7892-42fa-8242-44cba9a5065d Gather the ingredients.
4ff277a7-7892-42fa-8242-44cba9a5065d Add the unsalted butter and the vermicelli to a large sauté pan or pot that has a tight-fitting lid. Brown the noodles on medium-high heat, stirring often, and be careful not to burn them.
4ff277a7-7892-42fa-8242-44cba9a5065d Once the noodles are browned, add the rice and water to the pot and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce the heat down to low, and simmer for about 20 minutes or until the water has been absorbed and the rice is tender.
4ff277a7-7892-42fa-8242-44cba9a5065d Fluff with a fork, season with salt and pepper, and add in chopped parsley or toasted pine nuts, if using. Serve as a side dish to fish, chicken, or beef.
cb769bf0-fd2e-40b0-a4f2-4746ba621db3 Gather the ingredients.
cb769bf0-fd2e-40b0-a4f2-4746ba621db3 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
cb769bf0-fd2e-40b0-a4f2-4746ba621db3 Make the cheesecake filling by combining the cream cheese with the sugar, egg, lemon juice, sour cream (or Greek yogurt), flour and salt until fully mixed.
cb769bf0-fd2e-40b0-a4f2-4746ba621db3 Spread a layer of phyllo dough over each pan and brush with the melted butter. Add 8 more sheets to each pan, with melted butter brushed over each sheet. Allow the dough sheets to overhang the pan.
cb769bf0-fd2e-40b0-a4f2-4746ba621db3 Pour the cheesecake filling equally into each pan and sprinkle on the chopped pistachios. Fold the edges of the phyllo dough over the cheesecake. Don't worry about making it perfect. It will crumple up naturally. Brush on a little more melted butter and place on a baking sheet. Bake in the oven for 20 minutes, then cover the browned phyllo crust loosely with aluminum foil and continue baking for an additional 20 minutes.
cb769bf0-fd2e-40b0-a4f2-4746ba621db3 Make the syrup by adding the sugar, water, honey and lemon juice to a pot and simmering gently until the sugar dissolves. When the cheesecakes are done, remove from the oven and let cool just until you can remove them from the spring-form. Pour the honey syrup over each one and let sit for a few minutes to let it soak in.
cb769bf0-fd2e-40b0-a4f2-4746ba621db3 Serve and enjoy!
2af25623-60cf-4c27-bf20-e3f9b7fb8ab0 Preheat the oven to 400 F.
2af25623-60cf-4c27-bf20-e3f9b7fb8ab0 Unroll the puff pastry sheets and place them on greased baking sheets or ones lined with parchment paper. Bake for 15 minutes. You want the puff pastry to be golden and puffed. Remove from oven but do not turn the oven off.
2af25623-60cf-4c27-bf20-e3f9b7fb8ab0 Break the puff pastry into small pieces (about 1 to 2 inches). Place the broken pieces into a large bowl along with the nuts and coconut flakes. Be sure that they are mixed well and evenly distributed. Place the nuts and pastry mixture into a greased 9 x 12 baking dish.
2af25623-60cf-4c27-bf20-e3f9b7fb8ab0 In a saucepan, heat the sweetened condensed milk, vanilla, and water on medium heat. Allow to cook for about 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from the heat and allow to cool.
2af25623-60cf-4c27-bf20-e3f9b7fb8ab0 Pour the milk mixture over the puff pastry nut mixture. Pour the cream on top and bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
2af25623-60cf-4c27-bf20-e3f9b7fb8ab0 Serve warm or at room temperature.
4fcbdeed-810d-4e1b-adfd-3a2fd2e41bb3 Pre-heat the oven to 350 F and butter and flour a bundt or tube style pan.
4fcbdeed-810d-4e1b-adfd-3a2fd2e41bb3 Using a hand or stand mixer, beat together the eggs and sugar until lightened in color.
4fcbdeed-810d-4e1b-adfd-3a2fd2e41bb3 Beat in the butter, vanilla, and yogurt. Stir in the food coloring, if using.
4fcbdeed-810d-4e1b-adfd-3a2fd2e41bb3 Add the pistachios to a food processor and pulse until ground
4fcbdeed-810d-4e1b-adfd-3a2fd2e41bb3 In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, ground pistachios, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
4fcbdeed-810d-4e1b-adfd-3a2fd2e41bb3 Beat the dry ingredients into the wet and pour the batter into the prepared pan.
4fcbdeed-810d-4e1b-adfd-3a2fd2e41bb3 Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
4fcbdeed-810d-4e1b-adfd-3a2fd2e41bb3 Make the glaze by whisking together the powdered sugar, milk, cardamom, and salt until smooth.
4fcbdeed-810d-4e1b-adfd-3a2fd2e41bb3 Drizzle over the cooled cake and sprinkle on some additional chopped pistachios, if desired.
29d2def3-84d3-4c77-b616-0eadbe61498a Pre-heat the oven to 350 F and butter and flour a 9-inch cake pan. You can also bake this in a standard loaf pan.
29d2def3-84d3-4c77-b616-0eadbe61498a Using a hand or stand mixer, cream together the eggs, sugar, and honey until fluffy and lightened in color. Beat in the butter, buttermilk, and vanilla.
29d2def3-84d3-4c77-b616-0eadbe61498a In a separate bowl, sift together the all-purpose flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt. Mix the dry ingredients into the wet batter.
29d2def3-84d3-4c77-b616-0eadbe61498a Peel, core, and dice the apple. Tip: Toss the apple pieces with a teaspoon of flour to prevent them from sinking to the bottom of the cake.
29d2def3-84d3-4c77-b616-0eadbe61498a Fold the apple pieces into the batter and pour into the prepared cake pan. Bake for approximately 30 minutes or until a cake tester or toothpick comes out clean. Allow cooling before removing from the pan.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad Gather the ingredients.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad Preheat oven to 375 F. Spray a 9x13-inch cake pan with non-stick cooking spray.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad In a bowl, combine butter, egg yolks, coffee, sugar, and flour with your hands until the mixture is crumbly.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad Press the mixture into the bottom of the cake pan. This forms the base for the cake.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad In a separate bowl, combine eggs, white cheese, sugar, vanilla sugar, and flour.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad Pour this mixture on top of the cake base.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad Bake for 30 minutes or until the cheese does not wiggle. Remove cake and cool for 30 minutes.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad Turn oven temperature down to 200 F.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad In a small bowl, mix sour cream with vanilla sugar and sugar. Spread evenly over the cooled cake.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad Bake again for 20 minutes.
9d08ef96-3f32-47aa-98d1-707eb768c5ad Refrigerate until fully cooled and firm and then serve!
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Gather the ingredients.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Combine the sesame paste, butter, vanilla, confectioner's sugar and salt in a bowl and mix until thoroughly combined.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Use a small scoop (approximately 1 ounce) or your hands to form balls and place them on a dish lined with parchment paper.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Insert a toothpick into each ball to make them easier to dip in the chocolate.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Place the formed candies in the freezer to harden while you make the coating.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Place the chocolate chips and butter in a bowl set over a pot of simmering water and stir occasionally until melted.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Stir in the butter.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 At this point, the chocolate may seize up a little. If so, add the tablespoon of milk or cream and continue stirring until it's smoothed out again.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Remove from the heat and allow to cool for about 10 minutes.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Remove the peanut butter balls from the freezer and, gripping by the toothpick, dip each one about 3/4 into the chocolate.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Place them back on the parchment paper, sprinkle on a bit of sea salt and refrigerate for about an hour for the chocolate to set up.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Serve them with or without the toothpicks.
9d33c030-7bc0-4645-ba94-4fbf1c66ea76 Enjoy!
373a027b-9ec5-4739-b565-dcecaa1e9376 Gather the ingredients.
373a027b-9ec5-4739-b565-dcecaa1e9376 Cut the tips of the fig stems off, slice in half and add to a blender or small food processor.
373a027b-9ec5-4739-b565-dcecaa1e9376 Add the banana half, Greek-style yogurt, honey, salt, and 1/4 cup of the milk to the blender.
373a027b-9ec5-4739-b565-dcecaa1e9376 Puree until smooth and continue adding milk if you'd like a thinner consistency.
39f5a752-9ffc-4d1c-bed2-5f25054b2b38 Gather the ingredients.
39f5a752-9ffc-4d1c-bed2-5f25054b2b38 Heat the honey in a heavy-bottomed saucepan over medium heat until it reaches 240 F or the “soft ball” stage. (The soft ball stage is when syrup is dropped into cold water and forms a soft, flexible ball.)
39f5a752-9ffc-4d1c-bed2-5f25054b2b38 Allow the honey to cool slightly and add the vanilla and nuts.
39f5a752-9ffc-4d1c-bed2-5f25054b2b38 Gently fold in the tahini and stir until the mixture is well blended.
39f5a752-9ffc-4d1c-bed2-5f25054b2b38 Lightly oil a 6-cup mold, loaf, or cake pan.
39f5a752-9ffc-4d1c-bed2-5f25054b2b38 Pour the mixture into the pan and cool completely.
39f5a752-9ffc-4d1c-bed2-5f25054b2b38 Wrap the halvah well and refrigerate it for 24 to 36 hours so the halvah’s characteristic crystallized texture can fully develop.
39f5a752-9ffc-4d1c-bed2-5f25054b2b38 Cut the halvah while it’s cold but serve at room temperature. The halvah will keep in the refrigerator for months.
39f5a752-9ffc-4d1c-bed2-5f25054b2b38 Enjoy!
515817f6-a7fa-44c4-bcc9-a206c1740452 Preheat the oven to 350 F / 180 C. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
515817f6-a7fa-44c4-bcc9-a206c1740452 In a bowl, mix the egg, cheese, parsley, garlic salt, and pepper.
515817f6-a7fa-44c4-bcc9-a206c1740452 Using a sharp knife, cut the puff pastry into 5-inch squares.
515817f6-a7fa-44c4-bcc9-a206c1740452 Place a heaping tablespoon of cheese filling in each square.
515817f6-a7fa-44c4-bcc9-a206c1740452 Dampen the edges of the squares with water, and fold in half diagonally to form triangular pastries.
515817f6-a7fa-44c4-bcc9-a206c1740452 Pinch the edges together to seal the filling inside.
515817f6-a7fa-44c4-bcc9-a206c1740452 Brush the tops of the bourekas with beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
515817f6-a7fa-44c4-bcc9-a206c1740452 Bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes, or until the pastries are puffed and golden, and the filling is cooked through. Serve immediately.
cd5762f2-7598-4915-a6b5-537638071653 Gather the ingredients.
cd5762f2-7598-4915-a6b5-537638071653 Add the sugar to a heavy bottom pot and heat on low until it melts and starts to brown.
cd5762f2-7598-4915-a6b5-537638071653 Once the sugar is bubbling and a very light golden brown, pour in the heavy cream. (Note that the mixture will bubble up.) Begin stirring it until the cream is fully incorporated and then stir in the butter. You may find that the mixture has hard lumps. Just continue stirring, on low, until they melt and you have a smooth sauce.
cd5762f2-7598-4915-a6b5-537638071653 Stir in the tahini (sesame paste) and season with sea salt to taste. Allow the mixture to cool and then store in a lidded jar in the refrigerator for up to a week.
cd5762f2-7598-4915-a6b5-537638071653 Enjoy!
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa Gather the ingredients.
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa Make the tart dough by adding the all-purpose flour, sugar, salt, and butter to the bowl of a food processor. Pulse 10 to 15 times just until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa With the machine running, pour the ice water through the feed tube and continue running until the mixture forms a dough ball.
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa Wrap the dough in plastic and refrigerate for at least one hour.
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa When ready to bake, preheat the oven to 350 F.
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa Roll out the dough, on a well-floured surface, to about a 10-inch round.
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa Drape the dough over your rolling pin and transfer to a 9-inch tart pan, preferably with a removable bottom.
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa To make the filling, combine the mascarpone cheese, sugar, lemon juice and salt in a large bowl. Using a whisk or hand mixer, stir until the sugar dissolves and the mixture is combined.
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa Pour the batter into the prepared tart pan.
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa Place on a baking sheet and bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until the cheese is set and the dough is a light golden brown. Allow to cool thoroughly before removing from the tart pan.​
1e1576bb-1cf7-4e8e-a6bd-e3f64b25a0fa To make the topping, slice the figs and place them on top of the tart and drizzle with the honey. Serve with additional honey for people to drizzle if they like.
2090ee25-f548-4b19-a48b-4be13a4b4ad5 Gather the ingredients.
2090ee25-f548-4b19-a48b-4be13a4b4ad5 Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C. Line a baking sheet with baking paper. Set aside.
2090ee25-f548-4b19-a48b-4be13a4b4ad5 Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
2090ee25-f548-4b19-a48b-4be13a4b4ad5 Sift together the flour and cocoa powder and mix into butter mixture with a wooden spoon.
2090ee25-f548-4b19-a48b-4be13a4b4ad5 Fold in cornflakes and don't worry if they crumble.
2090ee25-f548-4b19-a48b-4be13a4b4ad5 Roll or press 1 1/2 teaspoons of the dough into balls and flatten them slightly. Place them about 2 inches apart on the baking sheet.
2090ee25-f548-4b19-a48b-4be13a4b4ad5 Bake in the oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven, and cool on a wire rack.
2090ee25-f548-4b19-a48b-4be13a4b4ad5 Prepare the icing by combining the icing sugar, unsweetened cocoa powder, and water in a bowl.
2090ee25-f548-4b19-a48b-4be13a4b4ad5 Mix well until the mixture is free of lumps and of a creamy consistency.
2090ee25-f548-4b19-a48b-4be13a4b4ad5 Spoon a little icing on each cookie, and decorate with flaked almonds.
48ecda23-7c8a-4e4c-97b4-dbaa418d0a1b In a food processor, grind the biscuit cookies into finely crushed crumbs.
48ecda23-7c8a-4e4c-97b4-dbaa418d0a1b Place the butter or margarine and chocolate in the top of a double boiler set over simmering water, stirring gently until melted. Or, melt in the microwave, heating in 30-second intervals, stirring between each, until smooth. Remove from the heat.
48ecda23-7c8a-4e4c-97b4-dbaa418d0a1b In a large bowl, use an electric mixer or sturdy spoon to combine the biscuit crumbs, melted chocolate mixture, sugar, cocoa powder and coffee granules.
48ecda23-7c8a-4e4c-97b4-dbaa418d0a1b While continuing to stir, slowly add the milk or soy milk until the batter is moist enough to hold together when shaped into balls.
48ecda23-7c8a-4e4c-97b4-dbaa418d0a1b Using clean hands, roll the mixture into walnut-sized balls. (Use about 1 tablespoon of the chocolate mixture per ball.)
48ecda23-7c8a-4e4c-97b4-dbaa418d0a1b Roll each ball into powdered sugar (or a mix of powdered sugar, cocoa, and cinnamon), coconut flakes, sprinkles, or sanding sugar.
48ecda23-7c8a-4e4c-97b4-dbaa418d0a1b Place on a plate, cover, and chill in the refrigerator until firm.
48ecda23-7c8a-4e4c-97b4-dbaa418d0a1b Store leftover truffles in an airtight container in the refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.
56a3af7a-969a-4c1b-8ad8-52bbcda01dde Gather the ingredients.
56a3af7a-969a-4c1b-8ad8-52bbcda01dde In a large bowl, whisk together the whole milk, heavy cream, honey, granulated sugar, vanilla, and salt.
56a3af7a-969a-4c1b-8ad8-52bbcda01dde Add the roasted pistachios to a food processor and pulse a few times until the nuts are very broken down but not powder or paste. Add the crushed pistachios to the bowl.
56a3af7a-969a-4c1b-8ad8-52bbcda01dde Pour the mixture into your ice cream maker and follow the manufacturer's instructions for proper use. Churn the mixture for 35 to 40 minutes.
56a3af7a-969a-4c1b-8ad8-52bbcda01dde Transfer to a freezer-safe container and freeze for at least 4 hours before serving.
56a3af7a-969a-4c1b-8ad8-52bbcda01dde Scoop and serve.
fff150ef-c7ce-4270-983f-2ac78e7022d1 If your ice cream maker requires pre-freezing the bowl, do so.
fff150ef-c7ce-4270-983f-2ac78e7022d1 In a large bowl, whisk together the whole milk, heavy cream, granulated sugar, vanilla, salt, and sesame paste (tahini).
fff150ef-c7ce-4270-983f-2ac78e7022d1 Pour the mixture into your ice cream maker and follow the manufacturer's instructions to churn for 35 to 40 minutes.
fff150ef-c7ce-4270-983f-2ac78e7022d1 Freeze for at least 4 hours before serving and garnish with the crumbled halva pieces if desired for a fun texture and flavor boost!
c7314eca-6d0c-43b3-a6cb-386d8f96dee6 Melt the semi-sweet chocolate in the microwave or a bowl set over a pot of simmering water. Allow it to cool slightly.
c7314eca-6d0c-43b3-a6cb-386d8f96dee6 Preheat the oven to 350 F and butter and flour an 8-inch square pan. Lining it with parchment paper will also help remove the brownies when they're done.
c7314eca-6d0c-43b3-a6cb-386d8f96dee6 Add the sugar and butter to a large bowl and, using a stand or hand mixer, cream them together until the mixture has lightened in color. Beat in the eggs, vanilla and melted and cooled chocolate.
c7314eca-6d0c-43b3-a6cb-386d8f96dee6 In a separate bowl, sift together the unsweetened cocoa powder, flour, baking powder, and salt. Add the dry ingredients into the wet and stir to combine.
c7314eca-6d0c-43b3-a6cb-386d8f96dee6 Cut the halva into 1/2-inch pieces and sprinkle them evenly across the bottom of the prepared baking pan. Pour the brownie batter over the halva and bake for approximately 40 to 45 minutes or until the tops of the brownies are set. Cool before slicing and removing from the pan.
667cc3b6-eaaf-4495-a71e-ee82f9e0a0ad Pre-heat the oven to 350 F. Butter a standard loaf pan and line it with a strip of parchment paper for easy removal of the bread after baking.
667cc3b6-eaaf-4495-a71e-ee82f9e0a0ad In a large bowl combine the eggs, sugar, and honey. Using a stand or hand mixer, beat together until the sugar is dissolved. Add the butter, vanilla and orange zest and beat until fully incorporated.
667cc3b6-eaaf-4495-a71e-ee82f9e0a0ad In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Add the dry ingredients into the wet and mix just until combined.
667cc3b6-eaaf-4495-a71e-ee82f9e0a0ad Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan and bake for approximately 40 minutes or until a cake tester comes out clean.
667cc3b6-eaaf-4495-a71e-ee82f9e0a0ad Make the glaze by whisking together the powdered sugar, honey, milk, melted butter, cinnamon, ginger, and salt. Drizzle over the warm cake.
4ff80b53-e330-46d5-b9c3-8cf4c91ce275 Add the frozen banana, Greek style yogurt, dates, ginger, milk, cardamom and salt to a blender.
4ff80b53-e330-46d5-b9c3-8cf4c91ce275 Puree on high until completely smooth, pour into chilled glasses and serve.
