4ff80b53-e330-46d5-b9c3-8cf4c91ce275 Note: Peel and quarter ripe bananas and place in plastic zip top baggies in the freezer for easy smoothies and frozen yogurt uses.
96f6f225-a37d-4700-906a-0e7926ec97bf Using a stand or hand mixer, cream together the eggs and sugar until lightened in color. Beat in the butter, sesame paste and vanilla.
96f6f225-a37d-4700-906a-0e7926ec97bf In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Mix the dry ingredients into the wet and then stir in the chocolate chips. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for about 8 hours or overnight.
96f6f225-a37d-4700-906a-0e7926ec97bf Pre-heat the oven to 325 degrees.
96f6f225-a37d-4700-906a-0e7926ec97bf Use a cookie scoop to form balls of dough and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Keep the dough balls at least 3" apart because the cookies will spread. I used a 2 oz. scoop and got about 14 large cookies.)
96f6f225-a37d-4700-906a-0e7926ec97bf Bake for 15 - 16 minutes until the edges are lightly browned. Sprinkle with sea salt and then allow the cookies to cool thoroughly before removing them from the baking sheet. The cookies will be very soft when they first come out and will break if you try to move them. Once cool, they will be firm enough to move but remain chewy in the center for a long time.
8b968466-c120-4082-8a40-b277c84f650e Add the pitted dates to a bowl and fill with the cup of hot water. Allow them to soak for at least 30 minutes. When ready, add the dates and about 1/4 cup of the water to a food processor along with the honey and salt. Puree until completely smooth.
8b968466-c120-4082-8a40-b277c84f650e To make the cookies, sift together the flour, sugar, and salt in a large bowl.
8b968466-c120-4082-8a40-b277c84f650e Cut in the butter using a pastry cutter or fork. You can also do this in a stand mixer.
8b968466-c120-4082-8a40-b277c84f650e Add the vanilla and buttermilk and stir until combined. Note that the batter will probably be too thick for a mixer and you will need to do this by hand.
8b968466-c120-4082-8a40-b277c84f650e Turn the dough out onto a floured board and form into a disk. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
8b968466-c120-4082-8a40-b277c84f650e Preheat the oven to 350 F. Roll out the cookie dough, on a well-floured surface, to about 1/4" thick.
8b968466-c120-4082-8a40-b277c84f650e Use a cookie cutter (mine was about 3") to cut out rounds and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
8b968466-c120-4082-8a40-b277c84f650e Bake for 12 to 14 minutes and allow to cool for at least 15 minutes before moving. The cookies will be very soft when you take them out of the oven but will harden after cooling.
8b968466-c120-4082-8a40-b277c84f650e Place a tablespoon of honey date filling in the center of one cookie and top with a second cookie to spread the filling. A 3" cutter will yield about 16 cookies which will be 8 sandwiched cookies.
595a9cfb-8267-40c6-8f0c-6cce1da7a014 Gather the ingredients.
595a9cfb-8267-40c6-8f0c-6cce1da7a014 Using either a stand or hand mixer, whip together the cream and sugar.
595a9cfb-8267-40c6-8f0c-6cce1da7a014 Beat in the yogurt, goat cheese, vanilla, and salt.
595a9cfb-8267-40c6-8f0c-6cce1da7a014 Pour equally into 4 jars or dessert glasses and refrigerate for about an hour to firm up.
595a9cfb-8267-40c6-8f0c-6cce1da7a014 Add the sugar, honey, salt, and water to a saucepan and heat on medium just until the sugar dissolves.
595a9cfb-8267-40c6-8f0c-6cce1da7a014 Distribute the halved figs evenly into the 4 servings and pour the honey glaze over the figs.
b754a253-7387-4f1f-8a07-e6fca377ddda Gather the ingredients.
b754a253-7387-4f1f-8a07-e6fca377ddda Add the butter and sugar to a bowl and, using a stand or hand mixer, cream together. Mix in the vanilla and milk.
b754a253-7387-4f1f-8a07-e6fca377ddda In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, salt and cardamom. Stir the dry ingredients into the wet and fold in half the chopped pistachios. Form into a ball, wrap in plastic and refrigerate for at least one hour.
b754a253-7387-4f1f-8a07-e6fca377ddda When ready to make the cookies, pre-heat the oven to 350 F.
b754a253-7387-4f1f-8a07-e6fca377ddda Roll the dough out on a floured surface till it's approximately an 8 inch circle. Use a 2 1/2 inch cookie or biscuit cutter to cut out rounds.
b754a253-7387-4f1f-8a07-e6fca377ddda Place the remainder of the chopped pistachios in a bowl and gently dip the edges of the rounds into the nuts.
b754a253-7387-4f1f-8a07-e6fca377ddda Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 20 to 22 minutes.
b754a253-7387-4f1f-8a07-e6fca377ddda After baking, allow the cookies to cool and firm up before removing them from the baking sheet.
b754a253-7387-4f1f-8a07-e6fca377ddda Serve and enjoy!
6e0b8a24-0c19-4bdf-9322-6498a33a4d76 Gather the ingredients.
6e0b8a24-0c19-4bdf-9322-6498a33a4d76 Heat the oven to 350 F.
6e0b8a24-0c19-4bdf-9322-6498a33a4d76 Using a stand or hand mixer, cream together the eggs and sugar until lightened in color. Beat in the butter and almond extract.
6e0b8a24-0c19-4bdf-9322-6498a33a4d76 In a separate bowl, sift together the salt, baking powder, and all-purpose flour (or, if making the Passover version, the potato starch and cake meal).
6e0b8a24-0c19-4bdf-9322-6498a33a4d76 Fold the dry ingredients into the wet, stir in the sliced almonds, and turn out onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. The dough will be very sticky and you'll need additional flour (or cake meal) to shape it into a loaf, approximately 3 inches high.
6e0b8a24-0c19-4bdf-9322-6498a33a4d76 Bake for 45 minutes.
6e0b8a24-0c19-4bdf-9322-6498a33a4d76 With a serrated knife, slice while the loaf is still warm.
7c6cb8b7-34d5-4c86-824a-c75fcf6edaa7 Gather the ingredients.
7c6cb8b7-34d5-4c86-824a-c75fcf6edaa7 In a small saucepan, bring the sugar and water to a boil.
7c6cb8b7-34d5-4c86-824a-c75fcf6edaa7 Once the sugar is dissolved, add the saffron and rosewater. You will have a syrup like texture. Remove from heat.
7c6cb8b7-34d5-4c86-824a-c75fcf6edaa7 In a medium saucepan, melt the butter on medium heat.
7c6cb8b7-34d5-4c86-824a-c75fcf6edaa7 Add the flour slowly and mix with the butter to make a paste.
7c6cb8b7-34d5-4c86-824a-c75fcf6edaa7 Slowly add the sugar syrup and blend together. Remove from the heat.
7c6cb8b7-34d5-4c86-824a-c75fcf6edaa7 Immediately pour the mixture into individual ramekins or onto a serving plate.
7c6cb8b7-34d5-4c86-824a-c75fcf6edaa7 Allow to cool and either remove the halva from the ramekins or cut into small serving pieces.
7c6cb8b7-34d5-4c86-824a-c75fcf6edaa7 Serve with coffee or tea.
e27bc215-e6e3-4864-bb80-e78dc3dff24a Rinse the rice well with cold water to remove any starchy coating from the grains.
e27bc215-e6e3-4864-bb80-e78dc3dff24a In a large saucepan over medium-high heat, combine rice and milk. Bring the liquid to a low boil and then reduce the heat to a simmer.
e27bc215-e6e3-4864-bb80-e78dc3dff24a Simmer until creamy, approximately 45 minutes. Stir the mixture occassionally to ensure the rice isn't sticking to the bottom of the pan.
e27bc215-e6e3-4864-bb80-e78dc3dff24a Add remaining 3 tablespoons of milk, sugar, cardamom, salt, and cornstarch to rice and stir thoroughly. Add rosewater and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
e27bc215-e6e3-4864-bb80-e78dc3dff24a Remove from heat and allow to sit for 5 minutes to thicken and transfer to serving bowls.
e27bc215-e6e3-4864-bb80-e78dc3dff24a Serve immediately or refrigerate for at least one hour.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 Gather the ingredients.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 Add the egg and butter to a large bowl and cream together using a hand or stand mixer.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 Beat in the sugar, orange zest, and orange juice.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 Fold the dry ingredients into the wet, turn out onto a floured surface to form a dough ball, wrap in plastic and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 While the dough is chilling, make the filling by adding the dates to a bowl with the hot water and let soak for 30 minutes.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 Add the soaked dates and about 1/4 cup of the water to a food processor with the honey and salt. Puree until completely smooth.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 Pre-heat the oven to 375 F.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 Roll the dough out to between 1/8- to 1/4-inch thick (I like thicker cookies). Use a 3 1/2-inch round cutter to cut circles out of the dough.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 Place about a teaspoon of honey date filling in the center of each dough round and fold into the classic triangular shape (see an easy tutorial here).
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
329273e5-fe33-4487-ace0-60e2219660b6 Cool and enjoy!
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b In a large bowl, sift together the all purpose flour, salt and baking powder.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b Add the olive oil and mix together until all the flour is coated with the oil.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b Add the cold water and continue mixing to form a dough ball.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b While the dough is chilling, add the beets to a pot of boiling water and cook on high heat for 5 minutes.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b Drain and allow to cool enough to peel and slice thinly. Note that a mandoline works best for this but you can also use a sharp knife.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b Pre-heat the oven to 400 degrees.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b Roll out the dough, on a floured surface, to about an 8 inch round.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b Place layers of the sliced beets about 1" in from the edge of the dough.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b Sprinkle some za'atar and a bit of the crumbled feta cheese on each layer of beets.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b Roll up the edges of the dough and pinch together. No need to make it perfect.
a51be734-a855-4b1e-8c46-4f086c2d996b Place on a sheet pan lined with parchment paper and bake for 40 - 45 minutes or until the dough is a light golden brown.
d54914f5-2528-41ce-8f2b-d0f7b7c46959 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
d54914f5-2528-41ce-8f2b-d0f7b7c46959 In a medium bowl, combine flour and semolina. Set aside.
d54914f5-2528-41ce-8f2b-d0f7b7c46959 In a smaller bowl, beat together butter for 30 to 45 seconds. Slowly add in flour mixture until combined.
d54914f5-2528-41ce-8f2b-d0f7b7c46959 Stir in milk, allspice, and orange blossom water.
d54914f5-2528-41ce-8f2b-d0f7b7c46959 Roll dough into 12 pieces.
d54914f5-2528-41ce-8f2b-d0f7b7c46959 In a small bowl, combine nuts and sugar. Set aside.
d54914f5-2528-41ce-8f2b-d0f7b7c46959 Grab your dough and push 2-inch circles into it, then place onto parchment lined cookie sheet.
d54914f5-2528-41ce-8f2b-d0f7b7c46959 Place about 1 teaspoon of nut mixture on top of dough. Fold and press dough together to seal the filling. Repeat with remaining dough and nut mixture.
d54914f5-2528-41ce-8f2b-d0f7b7c46959 Bake maamoul for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Preheat oven to 350 F. Butter a 15 by 10 by 1-inch baking pan.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 In a bowl, combine pistachio nuts and butter.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Take eight sheets of phyllo dough and layer them in the pan, spreading each sheet with melted butter as you go.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Spread about half of the nut mixture over the phyllo dough.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Cover with a buttered sheet of phyllo dough.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Layer five more sheets of phyllo dough, buttering each sheet as you layer.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Add remaining nut mixture and layer with remaining sheets of phyllo dough, buttering each sheet.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Using a knife, cut the baklava into 1 1/2-inch diamonds.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Bake for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 About 30 minutes before baklava is finished, combine sugar, honey, cinnamon, and lemon juice for glaze in a small saucepan.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Bring to a boil, making sure that the sugar is completely dissolved.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Reduce heat and allow the mixture to simmer for 5 minutes.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 When baklava is finished cooking, drizzle syrup over top.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Let cool.
d2a89ae5-b608-459f-8590-ce9ecdfccbd5 Serve and enjoy.
1e0fd494-5dca-459d-9487-67a0461387e9 Gather the ingredients.
1e0fd494-5dca-459d-9487-67a0461387e9 Preheat oven to 350 F.
1e0fd494-5dca-459d-9487-67a0461387e9 In a mixing bowl combine semolina, flour, turmeric, and baking powder. Stir to combine well.
1e0fd494-5dca-459d-9487-67a0461387e9 In a separate bowl combine butter, sugar, milk, and water. Add to dry ingredients and stir to make a paste.
1e0fd494-5dca-459d-9487-67a0461387e9 Pour batter into greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle with almonds.
1e0fd494-5dca-459d-9487-67a0461387e9 Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
1e0fd494-5dca-459d-9487-67a0461387e9 Allow to cool for 15 to 20 minutes and serve with your favorite coffee or tea.
07be148c-4ea6-4d2d-8cee-12cc6edc6cee First, line a large baking sheet with parchment paper. After dipping your dates in chocolate, you will place them on the sheet to set.
07be148c-4ea6-4d2d-8cee-12cc6edc6cee Stuff each date with the nut of your choice. Melt chocolate in microwave safe bowl for about 3 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
07be148c-4ea6-4d2d-8cee-12cc6edc6cee Using a skewer, dip each date in chocolate. Allow the excess chocolate to fall off by carefully rotating the skewer. Place dipped date on parchment and sprinkle with coconut flakes. Repeat with remaining dates.
07be148c-4ea6-4d2d-8cee-12cc6edc6cee Allow dates to set in the refrigerator for about 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
